animal.description:
Angel is a beautiful senior pointer who was dearly loved by her prior owner, but was unable to stay with her because of health issues. Angel herself is as happy as can be, even as she is dealing with some health issues such as diabetes and hip problems. Her diabetes is under control, but she will need to continue with regular vet care, and her hip problems are being helped with supplements. She has limited vision due to her diabetes, but that does not stop her from exploring the yard, house, or on walks.

She loves to go for a morning walk with her foster sisters. She loves squeaky toys and will even steal the toilet paper if she can find it, she truly has the heart of a young dog. Her tail is always wagging and she finds joy in the little things in life.

Angel is looking for a forever family that will love her and be patient. She would do best in a home that is on one level and does not have a lot of steps going in and out.

Angel is being fostered in Minnesota.

Complete the adoption form here : ADOPT ME

*Please be sure to read the adoption info/FAQ tab on our main website before applying for a dog.

animal.description:
PLEASE READ THE ENTIRE BIO ON THIS DOG BEFORE REQUESTING AN APPLICATION.  .  MANY OF OUR DOGS HAVE STRICT REQUIREMENTS FOR THEIR ADOPTION.

SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS FOR BUDDAH:
1.   another confident dog in the home.
2.  fully fenced yard
3.  a female adopter
4.  no children in the home

7 month old male Terrier/Doxie/Chihuahua mix, about 9 pounds.
He is a shy guy that needs time feel comfortable with you. Once he feels comfortable with you, he is your little shadow. He seems to only be comfortable with women. Warming up to the men in the home has not happened, so we are looking for a "hen house" for him. He loves to snuggle and lick your face. He is a bit of a toy hoarder and will collect all the toys on his favorite bed and guard them from the other dogs. He will try to play fetch. He is very food motivated and his crate is his safe place. He has done great with other dogs. In fact, he needs another confident dog in the home to help guide him. He will go for leashed walks, but really needs the "draw" of another dog to help him be comfortable. He would do best in a home with a fenced yard, as walking in busy environments is a skill that still needs to mastered. He is curious about the cat and chickens at his foster home but so far he does not have the confidence to chase them. This boy will need lots of time and patience to blossom into the gem that he is!

Adoption contract and fee applies.  All adoptable dogs can be met at adoption events hosted every weekend. For a list of scheduled events go to: https://www.facebook.com/SmidgetRescue/events .  Smidget Rescue is not a shelter, and dogs cannot be seen at the Rescue location. All dogs are fostered throughout the Puget Sound area and are brought to the events where they can be met by prospective adopters. Additional pictures of adoptable dogs can be seen at: https://www.facebook.com/SmidgetRescue/photos_stream?tab=photos_albums.   All adoptable dogs are spayed or neutered at 6 months of age or older, and always before being placed in their new homes.  APPLICATIONS CAN BE OBTAINED BY EMAIL ONLY. Adoption process includes application, meet & greet, home visit and reference check. Email Jamie at smidgetrescue@hotmail.com or click on the CONTACT link on this page.  PLEASE DOUBLE CHECK YOUR EMAIL ADDRESS BEFORE SENDING.  We get a fair number of incorrect emails and Jamie is not able to contact potential adopters.  Notice:  We do not ship dogs out of state.  If you live within a five-hour radius of Seattle, WA, (such as Portland, Vancouver B.C., etc.), we can arrange for a home visit.  If your home seems like a great fit for the dog you would like to adopt, you must then drive to meet the dog at one of our weekend events or at the fosters home.

animal.description:
Have you ever wanted a pet that loves you and your family and no one else? That will adore you and their pack, but outsiders are viewed with caution? Well meet Shirley. Shirley is semi-feral pup. She was born apx May 2018. Shirley was trapped with her siblings by animal control. It will take patience and trust to seek human company. Shirley is excellent with other dogs and seems to be just fine with cats. They will bond fiercely with their family and be a devoted and loving member of the family. All it takes is time and patience. Shirley is available for foster to adopt. This will allow Street Paws to provide all the help and support their new family needs to begin their lives together. Ferals make amazing pets with just a little time. They are normally very laid back and easy dogs once you gain their trust. A home with at least one other dog and a fenced in yard is a must. Contact us if you are interested in becoming a member of our growing Street Paws pack!

In her current foster home she lives with a Pitbull and 2 Yorkie's She has a doggie door that she uses, allows her foster Dad to let her on occasion but would prefer to come smell him when he is not looking. She likes to sneak everyone's food bowls and take them outside.

https://youtu.be/E8A4Ed-xgUg

No out of state adoptions.

To apply to adopt this pet please fill out a Preliminary Adoption Application at http://streetpaws.org/adoption-application/. This application does not commit you to an adoption. It is used to screen those interested to make sure the home is a good match for the pet. We verify vet history on current/previous pets to ensure pets have been spayed/neutered and vaccinated annually. Our adoption fee is $250 for all of our dogs. They have been given age-appropriate vaccinations, are spayed/neutered, dewormed, received flea prevention, heartworm tested and treated if necessary, and microchipped.

animal.description:
Maggie is a 5-year old 8 lb toy poodle who was hit by a car and the driver threw her in the garbage to leave her to die in Tijuana.  Thankfully someone heard her screams for help and she was rescued, brought to L.A. and we took her into our group.

Due to the car injury, her hind leg had to be amputated but she gets around well on three legs.  She is very loving and sweet and only has one tooth!  Maggie gets along with other dogs but she is an alpha personality and would do best around other dogs who are submissive.  

We are working on her house training, she is spayed, microchipped and up-to-date on vaccines.  If you are interested in Maggie, please complete the on-line application that can be found on our website: www.adoptmerescue.org or contact us for more information.

LOCAL ADOPTION ONLY

animal.description:
PLEASE FILL OUT AN APPLICATION FOR ADOPTION!  Please do not call the shelter, until you have completed an application and are ready to make an apt for a meet and greet. Inquiries will not be answered at this time.

Santa and his brother Elf came us as strays that were never claimed by owners.  They are recovering from mange currently and their hair is slowly but surely growing back.  Elf and Santa have lived a rough life living on their own since they were tiny pups.  They are about 6 months old.  They are quickly learning here that people aren't so bad after all.  They came is very shut down and now excited to see their favorite people.  All you need for these pups are treats, patience, love and positive training.  We have not tried these boys with cats yet.  Older kids 10+ may be best for these pups.  Are you really ready for all the work in raising a puppy? Please research POSITIVE training techniques before applying to adopt. We care very much about your application answers and they are reviewed for completeness and the best match.   Please fill out an application on the included link: https://threerivershs.org/adoption-app-2/

The adoption fee of $250 includes spay/neuter, current vaccines, microchip, free vet visit, 30 days of pet health insurance, puppy book, and engraved ID tag.

animal.description:
www.huskyrescueteam.org

If you have additional questions please email info@huskyrescueteam.orgMr. Jack is one handsome fella! His last owner wasn't the kindest to him, but that hasn't stopped him from being one of the sweetest boys on the planet! When we rescued him from the shelter he had a gouge under his eye, but it's healed up nicely now. Jack is a two year old Siberian Husky and he's a vocal lover!

Jack loves other dogs, but REALLY loves the ladies! He came into the rescue with his girlfriend Jill (also available if you're looking to adopt TWO!), but we quickly learned Jack is a ladies man. He loves all the ladies and would be fine in a forever home with or without Jill as long as he has a canine girlfriend. Can you say 'calling all the single ladies?' :)

Jack would like a forever home with a fenced yard. He loves all humans alike but hasn't been around children. He'd likely be fine with children ages 8 and older. He's fairly calm for a young Husky and has a really sweet disposition. He loves to sing and has the deepest voice! Video here: https://youtu.be/YIetjBnl5do

Jack can be transported for the right home. His adoption area is NJ to NC.

www.huskyrescueteam.org~~Husky Education And Rescue Team is a foster based rescue. Our dogs are in our foster homes all up and down the east coast. We do not have a facility in which you can visit. We find this a huge benefit because we learn our dogs and are able to educate our adopters on what it's like to have them live in your home. Part of our process, once pre-approved, is to speak with the foster for the dog you're interested in. If you're still interested in adopting from our rescue the first step is to complete our adoption application online at www.huskyrescueteam.org/apply

If you have additional questions please email info@huskyrescueteam.org

animal.description:
Thank you for your interest in adoption from Palmetto Paws. If you would like to be considered to adopt from PPAR please complete the online application on the home page. Completing an application does not guarantee an adoption. The age to be considered for adoption is 21.

We will not consider applications for those not able to meet/adopt on the next upcoming Saturday or at a time designated by the rescue. Adoptions are done usually on Saturdays as we are all volunteers who work full time during the week. Dogs live in private foster homes. We do not host events and there is no opportunity to view multiple dogs. 
We will not consider incomplete applications. We will not process applications that are not for a specific dog listed on petfinder. We do not process and "hold" applications. We do not ship dogs and we do not arrange transports. All adopters must be present to complete the adoption. If an adopter is approved we do a “meet and greet” with a specific dog or pup. If at the meet we all agree it’s a good match, then the adoption takes place at that time. Their is no opportunity to meet and adopt at a later date. Again, please only apply if you are available on Saturday and ready to adopt.

Please keep in mind that we do our best to make an educated guess as to the breeds of our rescued pets. In rescue we rarely see the parents puppies, and even when we do, they are usually mixed breeds as well. We will never promise a particular breed or adult size.

We do our best to put all info we have in the bio. We will not respond to inquires regarding information that is already detailed in the bio. 

 My name is Tessa. I am about 3ish years old and I weigh around 45 pounds. Adoptable pets are spayed/neutered (unless the rescue Veterinarian deems the pup/dog will need to be adopted on a SN contract), have age appropriate vaccines, are current on hw and flea preventatives and microchipped. 

Tessa resides in a foster home with dogs and cats. She is crate trained and house training is coming along. She is energetic and has enjoyed the dog park. She walks on leash but a fenced yard would be ideal.
Tessa will need to continue heartworm treatment post adoption
at our expense at our Vet downtown Charleston. For this reason we are looking for a local adopter.

All adopters are provided with a medical summary, a new collar and leash, an opportunity to go over basic training/pet care and help shopping for supplies if needed. 

 The adoption fee is $395

If interested in adoption please submit an application! The application is found on our home page at palmettopaws.petfinder.com

He can be a bit of an indoor marker.
In general, he’s young, loves to interact with people and easily motivated by treats so he is proving to be quite trainable. Owner surrender.

animal.description:
Our girl Eddy was surrendered with several other dogs to Rockingham County Shelter.  Most all the dogs were unsocialized and Eddy was young and had hardly if ever been around humans.    
We went and got her in September, and our trainer fostered her to get her to understand she is safe with us.  She has come out of her shell and is such a great girl.  She loves loves loves to play and her favorite play partner is our therapy pyrenees girl so size does not matter, just fun.
On first meet, it may take a little bit for her to warm up to you, but when she does, she will love you forever.  Just check out the pics with the trainer's son.
If Eddy is the girl for you please check out our procedures below
1. on line application
2. vet and reference check
3. phone call
4. home visit
5 meet and greet
6. adoption
We will travel up to two hours to do home checks. We also truly feel the dogs in our rescue have been through enough. We take in those who are injured, abused, neglected, sick, and abandoned. That being said we search for a home that they are never put in that position again and that fits their personality and needs the best. No more hurt or fear.
Link to app:
https://cliffordsarmyrescue.com/1423-2/

animal.description: Hi My name is Monkey and I am a 6 month old border collie mix.  I was born with a condition known as cerebellar hypoplasia (or CH).  It is a genetic condition in which the part of the brain that controls neuromuscular function doesn't develop properly.  As a result, I have a wonky walk and have difficulty with fine motor skills.  I also need help getting up if I happen to fall over on my side.  But...other than that, I am a healthy, happy, playful puppy!  I love to run around the backyard, play with toys and wrestle with the other dogs in my foster home.  When I have finally run out of energy, I want nothing more than to collapse in your lap for lots of pets and snuggles.  I don't care about cats and am good with kids.  I'm housebroken and up-to-date on my vaccinations.  If you are interesting in meeting me, please contact kathie@heridnghaven.org

IMPORTANT!!!   All adoptions are by appointment only going forward and are spaced 30 minutes apart. PLEASE call the shelter directly during business hours for more information (see number below).  You need to make sure that the animal in which you have an interest is still available and to set up an appointment to meet the specific animal.  Once you arrive at the shelter for your scheduled appointment, please follow the directions that you were given over the telephone. If you are running late for your appointment or will be unable to make your scheduled appointment time, notify staff immediately. This will enable them to schedule that time for another prospective adoptive family. If necessary, they will be able to reschedule your appointment to a more convenient time.  

As you can tell by his shelter name, COOKIE MONSTER was able to talk somebody on staff into giving him treats during his intake process!  This American Bulldog mix male is about 2 years old and he weighed 56 lbs. at intake in late December. He is brindle and has white markings. Notes on his cage card reflect that he is "very sweet" and "knows sit."  So, he has had at least some training by whoever previously owned the responsibility for this pretty boy.  Go meet him!  Call to schedule your adoption appointment.  He has not yet been neutered.  Please read the important information below.

Adoption fees are $80 for dogs.  Cat adoption fees are $50. Cash or check only. Please be sure to take the exact amount with you.

NOTE: All shelter fees are under review and may be changed or modified at any time without advance notice.

The shelter routinely vaccinates all healthy appearing animals upon their arrival at the shelter and deworms them.  Any animals not already spayed/neutered must have the procedure done through the veterinary clinic that contracts with the county before that animal can be released from the clinic to the new family. By state law, animals old enough to be given a rabies vaccine, must have that vaccine done, as well.  The vaccine is given by the veterinary clinic staff at a separate cost to the adoptive family. 

Hold periods for every incoming animal vary for several reasons including, but not limited to, whether the animal came in from the Cumberland County area, or from the City of Crossville, which contracts with the county for its animal shelter services.  Check with the staff to verify the availability date of every animal for which you have an interest.

For more information on this pet, call the shelter at (931)484-8525. The shelter is open Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, Friday, and Saturday from 10am to 2pm. Closed Wednesday and Sunday and county observed holidays.

animal.description:
Welcome to the Wonderful World of Rescue Dachshunds. Look around and read their bios. Find a few whose personality seems to fit well. Consider one of our Well Seasoned Seniors who are truly wonderful and have so much to offer. Need help finding the best fit? We'll help with that too. Please fill out an application and let's get you all matched up with a loving new "furever' companion and friend. You'll find the application on the "Available Dogs" page.

NOTE:

Adoptions to Central/South Texas residents only

Standard Adoption Fee Adult Dog: $250 ea. Puppy Adoption Fee: $300 ea. Reduced rates for Seniors dogs (10 and up). Reduced rates for pairs (when adopted together). All adoption fees are subject to sales tax per the State of Texas. DDRTX only adopts in Central/South Texas.

Email: ddrtxinfo@gmail.com Primary Website: www.DDRTX.org
Momma to Moe Joe Surprise and Curly SurpriseMissy Sage Surprise has been given that name because she had 2 little boys a few days after being in her foster home! No one knew she was pregnant! She is an excellent mom and has taught her boys well!

Miss Sage is about 2 years old and is a Black and Tan short hair beautiful dachshund mix. I believe mostly dachshund since she has shorter legs and a long body! She is very sweet but shy around people she doesn't know. She might bark right at first but when she gets comfortable she will wag her tail, roll over and beg for belly rubs! She sleeps with her boys at night, we've tried to keep them apart but she loves being with them.

She is house broken and has had no accidents in the house.

She is shy around people she doesn't know but usually warms up quickly. She is good with the other dogs in the foster home, don't know about cats.

Miss Sage has had all of her vaccinations and is microchipped and is heartworm negative. She has been spayed and is ready for a forever home of her own!
Love dachshunds and not ready to adopt or circumstances won't permit having a dog? How about being a sponsor or making a donation. Every one of our dachshunds receives excellent medical care along with day to day food, love and housing. Being non-profit, we rely on generous individuals like yourselves to help save these fur babies. You can do this specifically for one dog with the sponsor button on their webpage or a general donation on our "How To Help" page. Easy and quick through Pay Pal or your debit/credit card. You generosity is sincerely appreciated by all and is tax deductable. Need other ideas? You'll find tons of them on the How to Help tab. All contributions are tax deductable.

Diamond Dachshund Rescue of Texas is a non-profit 501(c)(3) volunteer organization with focus on rescue and adoption of pure breed Dachshunds. All dogs are fully vetted and housed on private property. Meetings are scheduled upon adoption approval. Thank you for your continued support to the rescue and shelter communities!
Opt to Adopt!

This is Prancer.  He is about 6 years old.  He came out of a home with 40 other dogs and is just enjoying his one on one time.  He is a good size at 12.3 lbs..  Has no problem eating when you give it to him.

We would guess he will need some work on housebreaking.  He is ok to go outside with his coat on but without a coat it is just too cold for that.

We have him on schedule to be neutered.  His shots are current, surprisingly he is heartworm negative, is wormed and micro-chipped. 

He will be available to go home on 1/14/21 but can have visitors now and be adopted.  He just can't go home until he visits with Dr. Mike to be neutered.  His eyes are clear - the picture makes them look foggy but that is not the case.

He needs an older and stable home - not small children on a daily basis. We were told he could be a little grouchy but we sure haven't seen that side of him.

In order to adopt you have to complete an adoption application - you will find that on our website at www.patriotsforpets.com under the 'Adoption' tab.  His adoption fee will be $175.00.

Due to the high demand for puppies/dogs we anticipate multiple applications on any of our dogs/puppies. We will review each submitted application, then contact the approved adopter via email. If that particular person has changed their mind we will move to the next approved adopter. Thank you for understanding. If you are interested please complete an application at www.arf-fresno.com   

We will be putting pictures up for Scooter later today or tomorrow. We estimate him to be about 7 -8 yrs old.  We just completed a dental on him so he is ready to start his new adventures with his forever family.  He is a silly boy who was relinquished to ARF as his family was no longer able to care for him.   He is adjusting to being here would much rather be in a home where he can spend his days with a family.  Please be mindful that we have no idea if he is house broken or was allowed on the furniture in his previous home.   





Adoption fee for this dog will be $150.00, which helps with the expenses for spaying or neutering your pet, all vaccinations, including rabies up to date, microchip, and any other grooming or medical care that was needed when the dog was rescued by ARF. 





If you would like to fill out an application online, you can go to our website at www.arf-fresno.com, click on the Adoption Section and complete the application.      

Animal Rescue of Fresno is located at 4545 East Dakota Ave., Fresno, CA 93726 Visit our website, facebook fan page or call us for our current ours. Call us at: 559-225-5715 website at http://www.arf-fresno.com and our facebook fan page address is https://www.facebook.com/AnimalRescueFresno 

 
Animal Rescue of Fresno is supported solely by donations from you. animal.description:
PLEASE READ THE ENTIRE BIO ON THIS DOG BEFORE REQUESTING AN APPLICATION.  MANY OF OUR DOGS HAVE STRICT REQUIREMENTS FOR THEIR ADOPTION.

8 year old male Toy Fox Terrier, about 12 pounds.
Pierre is the funny lil man you need in your life! He’s good with dogs and gentle kids. Pierre handles extremely easily and gets cute little zoomies when he’s excited. He is quiet and would adapt very quickly to apartment life. This cuddlebug loves to nap and wouldn’t be suited to an overly active lifestyle - but he loves walks! Although he sometimes gets into trouble due to how curious and smart he is, he learns quickly with correction. True to his Terrier self, this old man has mad hops! He can hop onto surfaces that seem way too high for a guy his size; counter tops, tables, etc. So he really needs to be watched closely or mitigated in a way that prevents such naughty behavior! While Pierre hasn't shown any aggression towards cats, he does want to play with them and may chase them when his terrier mode is activated! Owner surrender. 

Adoption contract and fee applies.  All adoptable dogs can be met at adoption events hosted every weekend. For a list of scheduled events go to: https://www.facebook.com/SmidgetRescue/events .  Smidget Rescue is not a shelter, and dogs cannot be seen at the Rescue location. All dogs are fostered throughout the Puget Sound area and are brought to the events where they can be met by prospective adopters. Additional pictures of adoptable dogs can be seen at: https://www.facebook.com/SmidgetRescue/photos_stream?tab=photos_albums.   All adoptable dogs are spayed or neutered at 6 months of age or older, and always before being placed in their new homes.  APPLICATIONS CAN BE OBTAINED BY EMAIL ONLY. Adoption process includes application, meet & greet, home visit and reference check. Email Jamie at smidgetrescue@hotmail.com or click on the CONTACT link on this page.  PLEASE DOUBLE CHECK YOUR EMAIL ADDRESS BEFORE SENDING.  We get a fair number of incorrect emails and Jamie is not able to contact potential adopters.  Notice:  We do not ship dogs out of state.  If you live within a five-hour radius of Seattle, WA, (such as Portland, Vancouver B.C., etc.), we can arrange for a home visit.  If your home seems like a great fit for the dog you would like to adopt, you must then drive to meet the dog at one of our weekend events or at the fosters home.

This is Dancer.  He is about 6 years old.  He came out of a home with 40 other dogs and is just enjoying his one on one time.  He is overweight for a Chihuahua mix and could use some good exercise.  He has no problem eating when you give it to him.

We would guess he will need some work on housebreaking.  He is ok to go outside with his coat on but without a coat it is just too cold for that.

We have him on schedule to be neutered.  His shots are current, surprisingly he is heartworm negative, is wormed and micro-chipped. 

He will be available to go home on 1/14/21 but can have visitors now and be adopted.  He just can't go home until he visits with Dr. Mike to be neutered.  His eyes are clear - the picture makes them look foggy but that is not the case.

He needs an older and stable home - not small children on a daily basis. We were told he could be a little grouchy but we sure haven't seen that side of him.

In order to adopt you have to complete an adoption application - you will find that on our website at www.patriotsforpets.com under the 'Adoption' tab.  His adoption fee will be $175.00.

animal.description:
www.huskyrescueteam.org

If you have additional questions please email info@huskyrescueteam.orgMy name is Jill and I am a 2 year old Siberian Husky. I have the most piercing blue eyes and a unique mask (markings on my face)! I came into the Rescue because my last owner wasn't very good to me and...I was pregnant. The Rescue helped my pups all find great homes and now it's my turn.

They say for a Husky I'm fairly calm. Don't know what they're talking about because boy do I like to get a few zoomies on in my foster's fenced in yard. But maybe they're right because after that I just want to cuddle on the couch. And all this love....I never knew what it was like to have all this attention and love. They even let me lay in their lap here. It's awesome! I soak it all up and I want my forever home to do the same for me.

In fact I've gotten so used to all this lovin that sometimes I get upset when my foster family leaves the house. I just want to be with them so bad! I'm sure that will get better after my hormones settle after I'm spayed at the end of January, but I definitely want my forever family to be around lots - even after this thing they call COVID.

I also like other dogs so if my forever home had another dog that would be okay too but it's not required. I really just want all my humans attention so any other dog would have to be willing to share. I am potty trained and don't mind the crate. I really love the teenaged human here but haven't been around small children. The Rescue says I need a fenced yard and while I haven't tried to escape or anything they'd like a home for me who has researched the breed. If you haven't, they'll definitely give you a Siberian Husky 101 crash course! I can be vocal at times so it's best if I don't go live in an apartment.

So I think that's all for now, but I'm so ready to start this next chapter in my life and can be adopted at the beginning of Feb. My baby making days are over and now it's all about ME! Please apply today to make me a part of your family! ~~~Love, Jill

Jill is being fostered in MD. Applied adopters must be willing to meet here in MD. Adoption area NJ to VA. ~~Husky Education And Rescue Team is a foster based rescue. Our dogs are in our foster homes all up and down the east coast. We do not have a facility in which you can visit. We find this a huge benefit because we learn our dogs and are able to educate our adopters on what it's like to have them live in your home. Part of our process, once pre-approved, is to speak with the foster for the dog you're interested in. If you're still interested in adopting from our rescue the first step is to complete our adoption application online at www.huskyrescueteam.org/apply

If you have additional questions please email info@huskyrescueteam.org

animal.description:
Carleigh (*tap taps the mic*): Hello. I'm a good girl who hopes some kind and patient person will give me a home and love me forever, but right now I really wish I could just hand the mic to this nice gentleman here who takes care of me...

Nice Gentleman (*taking mic*): Thank you, Carleigh, for agreeing to talk to everyone. I know how nervous you are, but you did very well, and you're doing better every day. Folks, Carleigh can be afraid of lots of things-new people, loud noises, being left alone. She's a good dog who is still learning boundaries and rules. She would do best with an experienced adopter, a home without children, and someone dedicated to continuing to let her blossom and feel safe, so her true personality shines. In the right environment, she will grow into a happy companion. Look, she's calmed down now. Carleigh, would you like the mic back?

Carleigh: Maybe not, but could you tell these people that I like going outside for fresh air, especially if I can go for a long walk or a car ride? And that I also like biscuits, and soft plush toys, and large dog beds? And blankets! Nothing's more pleasant than a nap under a blanket!

Nice Gentleman: Carleigh, you just told them. You're braver than you know!

Carleigh: Really? Well, here's what I do know-nothing feels better than hanging out with a patient person I've learned to trust!

If you'd like to take me home, please fill out an adoption application at this website-http://www.animalalliesrescue.org/adoption-application-and choose me, CARLEIGH! My adoption fee is $300 and includes all of my routine vetting, rabies and distemper/parvo vaccinations, deworming, spay/neuter surgery, heartworm testing, monthly heartworm prevention, microchip, boarding and transportation costs if applicable, and a free* trial offer for 30 days of 24PetWatch pet insurance!

*Dependent on meeting eligibility requirements: Dogs 8 weeks to 10 years of age and cats 8 weeks to 12 years of age. This offer is not currently available to residents of CA, PA or RI.

animal.description:
Nala is a 4 year old husky mix who is as sweet as a cinnamon roll. She loves puzzle toys and snoozing on a good couch. She also loves sniffing and exploring. She is a very food-driven, intelligent and trainable girl. She learned "Sit", "Stay" and "Come" in just a week! She would make a great family pet for a family with a fenced in yard. She is eager to please and wants to make friends with every human she meets. She does not jump up when greeting you, but puts her ears back and wags her tail as if to say "hello there, are you my new friend?" 

Nala is potty trained, has no food aggression, and does great with kids. She has lived her whole life surrounded by babies and young children. She seems interested in cats, but gives them a wide berth when in the same room if she can tell they don't want to be friends.

She is a definite couch potato who loves to nap on the couch. She also enjoys having access to a yard where she can run around and sniff everything a few times throughout the day. She really lights up when given the chance to explore a yard! For this reason, Nala will need to be adopted by an owner who has a fenced in yard attached to their property.

Nala's favorite things are chicken, peanut butter, and the chance to go outside and sniff things. She is not a fan of car rides or being left alone--she whines and gets anxious. She would do best in a home where someone is home all the time.

Nala has been tested for dog aggression and is NOT aggressive. However, she is what is called "leash reactive", which means she barks and lunges if she is on a leash or behind a fence and she sees another dog. When she is in a play group with other dogs in a yard, she is not aggressive, although she can bark a bit. (That's the husky in her.) Nala needs a home with a yard so she can get exercise WITHOUT encountering dogs while on walks. She will need an owner with patience who can slowly introduce and desensitize her to seeing other dogs when she is on a leash.

Breed: One of a kind

Weight: 35

Handsome and refined is the best way to describe our boy, SCOTTIE. For a 9 year old, he still has a lot of pep in his step! He loves to run around in a yard, and enjoys long walks. He's a goofy little guy and would do best in a home with adults and older children. 

Before you can adopt, please complete an adoption application on our website at pawscrossedny.org/dog-adoption-application! Once your application is approved, you will be able to call to schedule an appointment. If you have any questions, please email us at adoptions@pawscrossedny.org for more information. Please understand that we cannot hold any pets. All adoptions are done on a first come, first adopt basis for approved applicants.

The Shelter software system requires that we choose a predominant breed or breed mix for our dogs. Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable so for most of our dogs we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We encourage you to select your new companion by considering each dog's individual personality and pet qualities instead of relying on a breed label that is only a guess.

animal.description:
Bentley, age 5, and Hondo, age 2, are a bonded pair whose NC owner sadly had to relinquish them to our organization due to a a health crisis. She had taken both dogs in from neighbors who were mistreating them and gave them so much love over the last year that both resilient dogs are very well adjusted, obedient and happy! Both dogs are excellent with people, children and other dogs. 

BENTLEY, an American Bully mix, came to us with two large pendulous tumors growing from her rear. She underrated surgery to remove them on 12/30 and is doing great now! Biopsy results revealed:

Of the two pendulous masses, while both were subcutaneous mast cell tumors (i.e., under the skin and not OF the skin) with a low mitotic count, meaning they are also less aggressive/less active, the margins on the right sided mass were clear and complete, but the left sided mass had a deep margin that was incomplete. This means that cancer cells were at the edge of what was removed. Because this area is too close to the vulva to cut deeper, we are submitting additional testing on that tumor to understand the likelihood of recurrence, though there is no evidence of spread. As this tumor is likley lower risk, BENTLEY’s adopters will simply need to monitor the area for any regrowth/recurrence (about 15% risk.) In short, given the size and location of the masses, this is overall good news so BENTLEY and HONDO are ready to GO HOME!
 
To apply to adopt this bonded pair (we will not consider separate adoptions) within a 5-6 hour drive of NYC or their Western MA foster home, head to www.mrbonesandco.org/adopt or email elli@mrbonesandco.org.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Luna is a 1 -2 year old poodle / terrier mix. (We make no assumptions or guarantees that she is a hypoallergenic dog as we are not sure of her mix) She came into rescue with 3 fuzzy puppies who she took amazing care of! Luna was successfully treated for heartworm and will need to remain on preventive for the rest of her life. It is relatively inexpensive, depending on the brand you choose.

Her foster family describes her as an old soul. She is the type of dog who just lays back and observes everything around her. She does have playful spurts but for the most part she just lays on the back of the couch and watches the world go by!

Luna is a good girl. She has had a few accidents in her foster home (mostly when it rains) but for the most part will go outside to do her business. She is a people lover for sure. She does live with other dogs and tolerates them but we don't feel she would want to live in a permanent home with a high energy playful dog - that's just not what she likes and has no problem saying so. A calm dog like herself would be fine.

Luna has a fenced in yard in her foster home and we found out pretty quickly that she was an escape artist. So if you have a fence it will have to be in good condition with NO way for her to get out. Chicken wire buried at the bottom for example (chain link) with no gaps anywhere. Wood panels at the bottom (wood fenced) also with no gaps or she will find them. She is also a door dasher so once she knows how you come and go she will be quick to try join you! This is probably how she ended up pregnant and in rescue as she is great at her craft LOL.

We think Luna would do fine with kids who are respectful of her. She has not been cat tested but we can't imagine her having any issues with anyone. She is working on leash training and has done very well but she will need more work on this in her forever home.

Luna is spayed, up to date with vaccines, microchipped, flea/worm treated and treated for heartworm. Her adoption fee is $450

animal.description:
Bentley, age 5, and Hondo, age 2, are a bonded pair whose NC owner sadly had to relinquish them to our organization due to a a health crisis. She had taken both dogs in from neighbors who were mistreating them and gave them so much love over the last year that both resilient dogs are very well adjusted, obedient and happy! Both dogs are excellent with people, children and other dogs. 

BENTLEY, an American Bully mix, came to us with two large pendulous tumors growing from her rear. She underrated surgery to remove them on 12/30 and is doing great now! Biopsy results revealed:

Of the two pendulous masses, while both were subcutaneous mast cell tumors (i.e., under the skin and not OF the skin) with a low mitotic count, meaning they are also less aggressive/less active, the margins on the right sided mass were clear and complete, but the left sided mass had a deep margin that was incomplete. This means that cancer cells were at the edge of what was removed. Because this area is too close to the vulva to cut deeper, we are submitting additional testing on that tumor to understand the likelihood of recurrence, though there is no evidence of spread. As this tumor is likley lower risk, BENTLEY’s adopters will simply need to monitor the area for any regrowth/recurrence (about 15% risk.) In short, given the size and location of the masses, this is overall good news so BENTLEY and HONDO are ready to GO HOME!
 
To apply to adopt this bonded pair (we will not consider separate adoptions) within a 5-6 hour drive of NYC or their Western MA foster home, head to www.mrbonesandco.org/adopt or email elli@mrbonesandco.org. 

Special thanks to our surgeon, Dr. Daniel Spector, DVM DACVS-SA and the SS 2 team at @amcny for tackling BENTLEY'S difficultly positioned tumors and ensuring the surgical site was reconstructed to maintain full function, and to her foster mama, Janet and @sylvesterishelpful for making sure her aftercare was expertly attended to.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Two year old Zebu doesn't want to go to another home but his mom fears for his safety if she doesn't rehome him, due to conflicts with another dog in the household. If you have multiple dogs in your household or multiple pets of any kind, it's possible they won't always get along. In this case it has become dangerous for Zebu. He was a rescue a year ago who was so shy he had to be picked up and carried out to the car when he was adopted. He has since made huge progress with his mom's assistance. He is very playful, and knows sit, shake, laydown, and give me kisses. He's also a snuggly dog!

Here is the ideal "must have" home for him, because when he does go to new places he can be very nervous: a fenced yard, another nice dog for companionship (he has some anxiety when left at home alone), and a fairly quiet home with little change or coming and going. Zebu appears to be a cattle dog or a hound mix, with a soft silky coat. He is two years old, about 45 pounds, and has adapted well to this home. However an adopter needs to know that he cannot make an instant transition as easily as other dogs might. If you're interested in adopting, please start with an application found here: friendsofcampbellcounty.org, under the animals heading.

PLEASE NOTE: This pet has been posted by Friends of Campbell County Animal Control, Rustburg, VA. For questions about the pet, please email us at FOACinfo@gmail.com. All adoptions begin with an application, found under the "Animals" tab on our website, friendsofcampbellcounty.org. *We will not consider invisible fencing.

animal.description:
Zeus is a sweet German Shepherd puppy, born 7/9/2020. Zeus is social boy who loves all people, kids and adults, and currently lives in a home with teenagers and a younger child. He is a big, active pup so his foster recommends caution with any children under 6 years old. Zeus is excited to share outdoor adventures with you so a large yard with a 6-feet fence would be the perfect situation for Zeus to get the body and brain exercises that he needs! At this time, Zeus is cautious about other dogs, but would enjoy having another dog friend to play with at home; he's ready to make friends and doesn't mind sharing his food and toys. He has not been tested with cats. Zeus is a sweet, very smart boy and would love to have an owner who is home most of the day. In his foster home, Zeus is learning how to enjoy his kennel and how to take his dirty business outside -- every time! Zeus is still settling in with his foster family and more information will be available in the coming weeks.

The suggested adoption donation for Zeus is $450. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes.

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver.

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months.

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

animal.description: Dustin has a hard time deciding what he most wants to do - lick your face or go on walks. He loves walks so much that when he sees you getting his leash out, he'll do a dance, spinning in circles and jiggling his butt in delight. Then at home on the couch, he's a big face licker and super cuddler. And if you stop petting and scratching him, he'll nudge you with his paw. This quirky, playful boy also loves playing catch and stalking those silly squirrels for hours. And he may steal your socks and take them in the yard to hide them. He freaked out in the recent snow, zooming all over the yard. But if you need to be on your Zoom meetings, he's happy to just go off and snooze. He's also wonderful with his foster's kids, doing no mouthing, jumping or rough play. A smart boy, he's also completely house-trained and does well when home alone, roaming freely. This gentle, loving boy will love a home with faces to lick and kids of all ages to play with. Come show him a leash and he'll follow you home!

animal.description:
THEY BROKE THE MOLD WITH THIS SILLY GIRL

Cleo is LOADED with hutzpah and she LOVES to show it.

Need some levity and entertainment added to your home?  Cleo has the personality and wow factor to liven up any home situation.  She's full of life, loaded with drama, as only Frenchie's are and really makes it hard to have a bad day, if she had any say in there matter.

Cleo is about 8 years old and a very healthy, solid, 15 lbs.  Don't worry about that eye.  That is a very old injury that was never treated and our vets will be removing what's left of the eye and closing it up to prevent further infection or injury.  So to add to her already overflowing eccentricity, she will also be one eyed and all the more colorful.

Cleo is probably not a dog for the first time dog owner.  She has a big, strong personality that needs an equally strong-willed person to guide her and help her use her powers for good.  She's smart, silly, intense, alert, playful, loving, devoted, curious, outgoing and ready for adventure but she has a shy, skeptical side when meeting new people and appreciates respectful introductions, sprinkled with a delicious treat or two.  She loves toys, treats, mealtime, car rides, walks and is not a particularly vocal dog, though she has an entire repertoire of snorts, snuffles, squeals and squawks that are hilarious... And she snores

She's pretty much housebroken but will test your meddle in making sure she stays on task, especially in inclement weather.  She also crates very nicely, but needs to be reminded that whining will get her nowhere.  She had a horrible habit of jumping hard, on people, bouncing off them like springboards.  She's learned that is bad manners too but will test your convictions on that from time to time, just to make sure it's still a no-no..

Cleo loves to snuggle during downtime and is very affectionate and loving.  She lives with a variety of dogs and does well with them all and has a delicate detente with the dog savvy cat, that might falter with a less confident kitty.  Kids are not her favorite but those over 12 who can mean no, when they say no, would be fine.

So if you think you have the sense of humor that would make this girl a welcome addition to your home, please go to our website at www.allmuttsgreatandsmall.org/adoption and tell us all about you and why you think this girl is perfect for you.

Cleo is spayed, microchipped, up to date on five way and rabies vaccinations, is worm and flea free and will be ready to go after her eye surgery on February 5th..

Her adoption fee is $275


Please note:

*Inquiries submitted through Petfinder, are not the same as applications 
  submitted through our webpage.  
*Yes we do out of state adoptions.
*No, we do not transport. You must be willing to come and meet the dog and 
  take it home with you.
*Yes we do Canadian adoptions.
*If the dog is on Petfinder, it is still available.
*You must be 18 years of age to adopt
*If you submit questions about an adoptable dog, covered in the Petfinder bio, 
 we will not respond.
*We do not pick the first good application.  We pick the most suitable 
  application for the dog, out of all submitted.
*All correspondence is handled via email as time allows.  
* If you are not chosen, you will not be notified

For a more detailed explanation of our adoption process, go to www.allmuttsgreatandsmall.org/adoption and read "The Adoption Process" link

Meet Eva! Eva came into rescue when her family found that they were too busy to give her the attention she deserves.  Eva loves snuggles but also likes her “me” time so she does very well in a crate, and she hasn’t had any accidents in the house since she has come into rescue. animal.description:
Peanut is one super loving, compact guy, but he is a nut. Being a puppy, he's got high energy and likes to antagonize his foster pittie brother. But he's eager to please and eager to learn. He is responsive to his name and is great with his brother and my pittie. He eats slowly, so will sometimes get annoyed with Butter while they're eating, but he's becoming less guarded. 

He's learning how to sit and lay down, but is a little overexcited sometimes and will forget what he's doing- but he loves his snacks, so he gets back on track quickly. He goes up and down stairs with ease and plays at full speed outside. While he loves his attention, he likes to be independent and explore in the bushes and investigate whatever he hears outside. He's timid at first, but warms up to you fairly quickly, then good luck getting alone time. He's definitely a Velcro pup and needs to always be at the center of attention. He listens well when called to come back inside after going to the bathroom. He's great with going to do his business outside and not in the house. We're working on crate training for two hours at a time and they do not whine or cry.

Please apply at thepitbullpen.org
Location: fostered in Portland, Oregon
Adoption fee: $450

animal.description:
Butter is smooth, much like his namesake. He's quiet and timid at first but next thing you know, he's crawling up into your lap. He's a big snuggler and loves to be carried. He also loves all the toys! He'll hoard them and surround his bed with them, and frankly, it's adorable. He's not possessive and doesn't guard them at all; he just wants to surround himself. 

He does well with his brother and his foster brother, a pittie. He will play and play once he's comfortable. He's not very vocal, though he'll whine to let you know it's time to go outside. As a fast learner, he picked up potty training and is getting the hang of sit and fetch. He's great in his crate and is perfectly content so long as he has a toy, and a bed (or a lap). He's very adaptable and just wants to be loved.

Please apply at thepitbullpen.org
Location: fostered in Portland, Oregon
Adoption fee: $450

animal.description:
Hi I'm Alfred, but my foster mom calls me Freddy. I am a handsome young pup and sweet as can be. My foster mom thinks I am going to be a big boy when I grow up. I am crate trained, house trained and get along well with my foster dog sister, although she is older and sometimes gets grumpy with my lack of personal boundaries. Because I am a puppy I am still learning proper manners like not jumping, being mouthy, and chewing on things, but am eager to please and already doing better. I I love to play with my toys and chew on bones, but my favorite thing is being with my human and cuddling. My foster mom thinks I would do best in a home that can give me lots of attention and patience since I am still learning the rules. I love kids but would do best in a home that has older kids because I like to knock tiny humans down. I would also love to have a furry dog brother or sister to play with so I don’t get bored. I can’t wait to find my forever home.

Email info@habitat4paws.org for an application.

**Because we require home visits, we only adopt locally to the Dallas/Fort Worth area. For more on adoption policies, please see the Adopt page of our website, www.habitat4paws.org.

animal.description:
**If you are interested in adopting one of the puppies, please download and fill out an application from our website www.forgottendogsrescue.com. The puppies' adoption fee is $450, and they will come to their adopters spayed/neutered, microchipped, with age appropriate vaccinations, and several dewormings.** 

Juniper is an active, playful, smart and feisty little girl! She'll do well with an adopter who will keep up with her energy level and keep her busy. She's a bit hesitant of adult dogs right now so should have an adopter who either has another adult dog in the home, or someone who will be able to set up lots of playdates with other known dogs to make sure she grows up to be well socialized. Juniper loves all people and kids and after she's worn out from playing, loves snuggling and getting belly rubs.

We are now accepting applications for our 20 puppies, the cookie and spice litters!

See more photos of all of the puppies on their Facebook album: 
https://www.facebook.com/media/set?vanity=forgottendogsrescue&set=a.3921486117870156

In November, we were contacted by our partners at Yakima Valley Pet Rescue (YVPR) to help with these litters of puppies. YVPR had taken in two pregnant moms (who were both in the same household) and were able to get them into one of their foster homes where the puppies were then born.  Unfortunately, the owners of the mom dogs only agreed to let YVPR (and, subsequently, us) take the puppies under the condition that the moms get returned to them but YVPR is going to ensure the moms spayed so they don’t have to go through this again. We would love to take the mom dogs as well but, this is out of our control and we are happy to, at least, help their puppies. 

As with most of our pups, we aren’t sure of their mixes but the moms appear to be part Pit Bull type dogs.  They are not related but, we think the puppies may all have had the same dad as there was a Pit Bull roaming around the area and the puppies were born within a day of each other.  Of course, this is all conjecture.  

The Cookie litter (9 puppies) were born on 10/30 and the Spice Litter (11 puppies) were born on 10/31. 

Cookie Litter:
Chocolate Chip - Male
Macaroon - Male
Samoa - Male
Biscotti - Male
Gingersnap - Female
No-Bake - Male
Rum Ball - Male
Macadamia - Male
Molasses - Female

Spice Litter:
Ginger - Female
Nutmeg - Female
Pepper - Male
Cocoa - Female
Cinnamon - Female
Caper - Male
Poppy - Female
Clove - Female
Dill - Male
Chipotle - Male
Juniper - Female

The pups have all been in loving foster homes in groups of 2 and 3 for the last month, and have been socialized, exposed to lots of new things, and have started working on house and crate training.  Several have been with kids or kitties or adult dogs or all of these or some of these. We will be working closely with each approved applicant to determine the best fit for the adoptive puppy and the family based on what we know about their personalities and temperaments. 


Please note that due to a large influx of applications we get for puppies, it can take several weeks for us to finish reviewing and processing them to find the best match for each individual puppy. Once adoption applications are approved, meetings will be set up with approved applicants, and, as mentioned, more information on individual puppies’ temperaments will be given and we will be working with each applicant to determine the best fit for the puppy and their prospective family.

animal.description:
his Mona Lisa is sure to make you smile!

Our girl is a 3 year old Terrier mix of some sort, weighing in at 35 lbs.

Sweet and submissive this little lady is crate and potty trained. Even a dog door is no hurdle for her. She loves to play with other dogs and is great with children.

Our Mona Lisa is still finding her feet in her new surroundings and is learning that the world is not a bad place after all.

Mona is a dog's dog but blossoms into a people dog if given time and space. She is initially shy with new people until she figures out no one is out to hurt her. If you already have a playful pup to show her the ropes and play with her she will come around in no time. A secure fenced in yard is essential to keep this girl happy and safe.

She is gaining confidence and trust in humans more and more each day but will require a family who can dedicate the time she needs to overcome her past and focus on her happy furever future.

All of our animals are fully vetted which includes spay/neuter, up to date on vaccines, wormed, heartworm tested and treated if necessary, up to date on flea/tick/heartworm prevention and microchipped) prior to adoption.

To start the adoption process please copy the below link in your browser and complete the application.  NOTE:  please read our requirements located above the application.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeotmh7qepR0mRvxSqy42yViQnllmR0-FKTFmUo2ANK4AXPaQ/viewform

Thank you for reading and THANK you for choosing to adopt!

animal.description:
Tim Tam came to us as the Dad of a couple of puppies and as usual, the puppies got adopted from the shelter and he was left behind. Before that he proved to be a great Daddy. Tim Tam is getting used to life in the big city of Los Angeles as he came from rural Central California and, based on what was done to his ears, has not had an easy life. Our busy streets are intimidating to him.  Some of our volunteers have spent time with him and he is gentle, sweet and loving, he just needs to know he is SAFE in order to relax. He will need some time to adjust to a new environment and city life. Tim Tam would do well in a home with a safe, private yard and can live with another dog who will help him continue his progress in building confidence. He is a handsome and very sweet boy.  
In the meantime, Tim Tam is looking for a foster home so if you’re interested in fostering this beautiful boy, please complete our  application https://www.therealbark.org/adoption-app

animal.description:
COMING SOON. This dog is not ready for adoption yet but please follow us theREALbark on FaceBook and @therealbark on Instagram to see updates on her progress.


Lorna is a sweet, smart, quiet and very shy lady.  Once she knows she is safe, and with a proper introduction, she is good with other dogs. She is in a foster home with two other nice dogs and does well with them.  She is super shy with people but learning how to trust them through her foster brothers.  She would do best in a home with a safe yard as she needs some lady-like privacy for her bathroom breaks. A calm household is a must and another dog who is nice tempered would be great, and children who are older than 16 would be fine. Lorna is still scared of loud noises, that is a work in progress both in the home and outside. She LOVES her walks now with her foster brothers and we hope we will continue to love her walks in her new home with a strong foundation. She will need a home with an adopter who understands rescue dogs who may have been neglected and not had a great relationship with people. Someone who will have the patience to continue working with Lorna on her progress. She is crate trained for a couple of hours only.

animal.description:
MEET MARTA!

This darling was surrendered to a vets office because her owner was not able to care for her. At first we thought she had limited vision in one eye, but we got a second option at our vet and after a full eye exam, it's been discovered she has her sight in both eyes!! The vet guessed Marta is around 12 weeks old and most likely a pit mix of some sorts. She's a happy wiggly girl and can't wait to find a forever home! She would do best in an active home committed to puppy training.

Pit bull & strong breed adoption criteria
- Must be over 25 years of age to adopt a Pit Bull, Pit Bull mix, or strong breed dog.
- Written landlord permission or a pet policy allowing the specific breed is required for adoption approval.
- A virtual home visit may be required.
- Training or breed experience is required as part of the adoption.
- Agree to not take the dog to dog parks or dog daycare.

If you are interested in meeting please fill out an application at our website www.gobeyondrescue.org/adopt. Our adoption fee is $350 and includes spay/neuter, microchipping and up to date vaccines. We Adopt in the SF Bay Area Only.

animal.description:
MEET IZI!

This tiny chocolate-colored boy is named Izi! Izi is an 11 year old Chihuahua who was surrendered to the shelter because his former family was moving and couldn't bring him along. Luckily, he found his way to City of Elderly Love and is now hoping to find the perfect retirement home! 

Izi is relatively quiet, calm and loving. He loves to spend his time with his foster family and will follow you room to room to see what you're up to. He'll occasionally get a spurt of energy and want to play but his favorite place to be is cuddled up on the couch next to you. Though he's a little guy, he's not the stereotypical yappy small dog though he'll bark at unexpected loud noises or knocks at the door like most dogs. He can be a bit nervous which is why he prefers to stay by your side. Izi loves to go for walks and because he's a little guy with a little bladder, he does need to go out several times a day. He's working on his crate training skills and will sometimes have an accident if left too long. Izi is currently living in foster care with other dogs and cats. He's comfortable sharing his space with them but would prefer a home with other low-key animals like himself. Though he hasn't met anyone he doesn't love, we think he'd be happiest in a home with older children due to his size and love of leisure.

Izi has received a veterinary workup since coming to the shelter and has been diagnosed with a Grade IV (of VI) heart murmur. He is currently on three medications to help with the heart condition (pimobendan, furosemide, enalapril). He has a cardio workup scheduled in February which will be at the cost of the rescue. Due to his heart murmur, he cannot receive a dental cleaning until he has been cleared by the cardiologist, which will also be at the cost of the rescue.

Izi is available for adoption through City of Elderly Love. He is neutered, vaccinated and microchipped. He is also heartworm and lymes disease negative. Interested in adopting him? Visit www.cityofelderlylove.org to complete an online adoption questionnaire or email us at info@cityofelderlylove.org!
animal.name: IZI!

animal.description:
Meet Baxter. Baxter is a chihuahua mix. He weighs about 15 pounds. (I am surprised he isn't a little more from all the treats he receives. Everyone loves him at the shelter) Baxter has been at the shelter for about 6 months to 1 year. He has been at the shelter a while due to his trust issues. A little backstory on Baxter... He was rescued in a garage. We aren't sure if he was abused or just ignored his whole life. We can't change Baxter's past but we can change his future.  Baxter has came a long way with our volunteers!! We are so proud of this little guy. He does a happy puppy tail wag when we give him treats or talk to him in a baby voice. 

"If Baxter could talk, I'd say he would have some tales to tell. You have to meet him, spend some time with him and let him give you the once over. He is a sweetie once you guys know each other"

Baxter is older and we hope that doesn't scare you away. Baxter would do best in a home with NO little kids and no super energetic pups. Quick movements can spook him and maybe cause a low growl. Baxter does do well with older and/or senior dogs. Looking to start a new series on Netflix? Baxter would love to join you on the couch!! 

If you are interested in meeting Baxter please fill out an application here http://www.treasuredfriendsrescue.org/?page_id=1281

If you can't adopt please share Baxter's story. The more people know about him the higher chance he could find a forever home!

animal.description:
**If you are interested in adopting one of the puppies, please download and fill out an application from our website www.forgottendogsrescue.com. The puppies' adoption fee is $450, and they will come to their adopters spayed/neutered, microchipped, with age appropriate vaccinations, and several dewormings.** 

We are now accepting applications for our 20 puppies, the cookie and spice litters!

See more photos of all of the puppies on their Facebook album: 
https://www.facebook.com/media/set?vanity=forgottendogsrescue&set=a.3921486117870156

In November, we were contacted by our partners at Yakima Valley Pet Rescue (YVPR) to help with these litters of puppies. YVPR had taken in two pregnant moms (who were both in the same household) and were able to get them into one of their foster homes where the puppies were then born.  Unfortunately, the owners of the mom dogs only agreed to let YVPR (and, subsequently, us) take the puppies under the condition that the moms get returned to them but YVPR is going to ensure the moms spayed so they don’t have to go through this again. We would love to take the mom dogs as well but, this is out of our control and we are happy to, at least, help their puppies. 

As with most of our pups, we aren’t sure of their mixes but the moms appear to be part Pit Bull type dogs.  They are not related but, we think the puppies may all have had the same dad as there was a Pit Bull roaming around the area and the puppies were born within a day of each other.  Of course, this is all conjecture.  

The Cookie litter (9 puppies) were born on 10/30 and the Spice Litter (11 puppies) were born on 10/31. 

Cookie Litter:
Chocolate Chip - Male
Macaroon - Male
Samoa - Male
Biscotti - Male
Gingersnap - Female
No-Bake - Male
Rum Ball - Male
Macadamia - Male
Molasses - Female

Spice Litter:
Ginger - Female
Nutmeg - Female
Pepper - Male
Cocoa - Female
Cinnamon - Female
Caper - Male
Poppy - Female
Clove - Female
Dill - Male
Chipotle - Male
Juniper - Female

The pups have all been in loving foster homes in groups of 2 and 3 for the last month, and have been socialized, exposed to lots of new things, and have started working on house and crate training.  Several have been with kids or kitties or adult dogs or all of these or some of these. We will be working closely with each approved applicant to determine the best fit for the adoptive puppy and the family based on what we know about their personalities and temperaments. 


Please note that due to a large influx of applications we get for puppies, it can take several weeks for us to finish reviewing and processing them to find the best match for each individual puppy. animal.description:
NAME: SARAH JESSICA PARKER

AGE/GENDER: 2 year old female

BREED: Thai street dog

TEMPERAMENT: Loving, low-maintenance

WEIGHT: About 30 lbs

HOUSE TRAINING: Good

CRATE TRAINING: Good

OTHER DOGS: Sarah Jessica Parker will do best as the only dog in the home.

CATS: TBD

CHILDREN: Dog-respectful children, 8 and older

ADOPTION DONATION: $450

HEALTH: Sarah Jessica Parker had a severe wound on her foot (now healed) and had a previous hip surgery. She has recovered well and is able to go on leisurely walks.

Your adoption donation goes toward offsetting the cost of this vet care as well as other incidental costs of care.

HISTORY: Sarah Jessica Parker came to us from our friends, Soi Dog Foundation. She was brought to the shelter as a puppy with a severe foot wound. Sadly, she was in the shelter for 2 years.

Motley Zoo Animal Rescue was asked to find her a great forever family and that is exactly what we plan to do!

NOTES FROM FOSTER HOME: Sarah Jessica Parker is a very sweet girl. She loves to go for walks but, due to her previous hip surgery, she prefers walks around the neighborhood over hikes or long treks. She is nervous around loud noises, young children, and lots of commotion. She is still growing her confidence and can be shy, but is a total love.

All dogs adopted from Motley Zoo come with a leash and Martingale collar (or a harness, if necessary), depending on each dog's particular needs. Each dog also receives a "Tour Gear Bag" full of brochures, coupons, and supplies for your new pup!

ABOUT MOTLEY ZOO:

Welcome to Motley Zoo Animal Rescue! We are a rock and roll themed, volunteer-run, foster based, 501(c)(3) non-profit animal rescue organization based in Redmond, WA.

Motley Zoo is a FOSTER BASED organization, which means our rescue animals are cared for in private foster homes (or partnering pet stores) where the animals receive one-on-one care and attention in a home environment until permanent placement is found. We do not have animals available for casual viewing and same day adoption. Due to the volunteer run structure and decentralized/ virtual nature of a foster based group, an approved application is required to make an adoption appointment for any of our animals.

If you are interested in one of our Adoptable Roadies, please email adopt@motleyzoo.org and request an adoption application (the auto-responder also has a link to our application). We will work toward getting you approved as an adopter so that we can set a time for you to meet your new best friend!

Motley Zoo also runs "Rock Star Treatment Dog Daycare" in Redmond, WA where proceeds from this service, help support our rescue's vet budget- however, this is NOT a shelter. For more information about daycare or training, check out www.rockstartreatment.org.

Please visit our website www.motleyzoo.org for more information!

Thanks for considering adoption- we look forward to helping you find your best match in a furry friend.

Rock on-

The Motley Zoo Crew

animal.description:
~~~~~
We are SO SORRY TO ADVISE YOU ... We are NO LONGER ADOPTING TO MASSACHUSETTS RESIDENTS DUE TO STRICTER AND UNATTAINABLE REGULATIONS !!

Liam is a 1 year old Blue heeler. He was snagged off of a very busy  6 lane highway in Louisiana  - we can only imagine that he got there due to the horrible intentions of someone.....  
He was brought to the vet and cleaned all of the wounds from running (in broken glass ; presumably)  brought to safety and we waited for almost a MONTH to re-unite him with his owners... and we waited.... Surely SOMEONE is missing this great guy- He is great with kids.... with dogs... and even (surprisingly) the resident cat!    He is NOT the typical Cattle dog- perhaps that is why someone dumped him.  He is well mannered and HOUSE TRAINED and is not UBER hyper as many ACD's / Heelers  are .. what a find! A diamond in the rough!  (RUFF) 





~~~~~

Due to Covid-19 concerns, we are not planning any public adoption events. If you are pre approved , we will call to set up an appointment to come and meet the dog and potentially take them home. It is by appointment only- 
Dogs will be brought into the outdoor kennel for you to meet and make your decision. MASKS WILL BE MANDATORY to maintain EVERYONE'S safety  NO EXCEPTIONS PLEASE !! Unless otherwise noted, the puppies and dogs listed will arrive on Saturday, January 23rd 2021 .
Please follow this link to fill out an application. It is step one in adopting a pup from our rescue.
http://littlerhodyrescue.com/adoption-application/ 
 

*Filling an application does not guarantee you as the adopter. All applicant's references will be called. PLEASE call your veterinarian and personal references and allow consent to speaking with us ! 
We cannot process your application otherwise. Failure will put your application in 'Limbo"  
We process applications as they arrive. The first approved applicant will be called and the pup taken off of Petfinder. We do not have the man/ woman power to all all other applicants to advise them. 
IF there s another dog that you are interested in as well, please list at the top of the application and we will enter your application for that pup if the first choice has been adopted. 

THANK YOU !!! You are giving a first rate dog a second chance....By adopting! 

***** SADLY , we need to put this in print: THIS IS A RESCUE DOG. We do NOT know their birthday / age.  (unless other wise noted)  
More often than not, OUR TEAM  has saved them from euthanasia in Southern shelters. 
We do not know any more than our Veterinarians offer to us. 
 We often have them in kennels, and utilize crate training.  House training status is often NOT KNOWN. 
Prior Health, estimated weight  (as an adult), breed (Including the parents' breed , size or mix)   and some health concerns are  NOT KNOWN unless our veterinarians discover it and offer the information to us.   Again, these are strays and turn ins from all over the country. They do NOT come with labels; nor guarantees. 

Characteristics and disposition can and will evolve with time.
YOU the adopter are responsible to train and keep up to date on vaccines and preventatives.  
YOU the adopter are responsible for taking care of this new member of your family. 
 *************

****
Our adoption fees are $ 600. This fee includes the transportation of the pet from one of the organizations that we work with in TX, LA or TN. Before joining us in RI all dogs are: spayed/neutered, microchipped, up to date on age-appropriate vaccines, and on de-wormers, flea/tick and heartworm prevention. In addition, all adults (6 months +) are heartworm tested and MUST be negative for both heartworm and microfilaria before transport. 

In addition to the above, all dogs must have a Certificate of Veterinary Inspection and be deemed healthy per USDA law in order to travel. Once they have been certified they are then transported via USDA transport services only, which is required by law. 
 We  sometimes don't understand how bad the situation is for these pups and dogs in southern states.  Many people in the south don't spay or neuter their pets as we do here. Subsequently, there are thousands of beautiful , worthy pups and dogs, kittens and cats  that are dumped, shot, abandoned, brought into shelters, neglected, abused and abandoned.  We step in , tend to their veterinary needs. As you can see above, we never fail to properly spay and neuter. Everything is done with the  caring , capable hands of our veterinarians to get them healthy and ready to place them for adoption. That's when we put the demand for family- friendly pets with the supply ..... 

Give a first rate dog a second chance!!!! ADOPT! 


Keep in mind that we also offer a two week return policy for the return of a healthy dog that includes a full refund. We want to make sure that the adoption is a perfect fit for both you and the dog.

If you would like more information about adopting please select "More About Little Rhody Rescue" where you will also find our online application if you'd like to proceed with the adoption process. Thank you!

animal.description:
ADOPT ME ONLINE: https://ophrescue.org/dogs/10350

Hi! My name is Grand Teton and I'm part of the National Parks transport that came to OPH 1-8-21! I'm guessed to be a terrier mix and I weigh about 55lbs. I'm a sweet girl and I am about 4 years old. Being a former mother, I am gentle, loving, and protective. I love going on long walks, meeting new people and dogs (though a bit shy at first), and absolutely LOVE to cuddle. I'm athletic and love hanging out. 

Grand Teton is a medical miracle. Her body has recovered from severe injuries in amazing ways naturally, which can be viewed as a testament to her physical strength and health as well as overall resilient nature of her character. She does cope with being crated, but it is not her favorite. She is playful, but doesn't play with toys. She is friendly with other humans as well as other pets so long as they're not aggressive. She is great walking companion - no pulls. Generally, she is the perfect balance of social and submissive. She is curious, but listens very well. She is also very intelligent and can be trained easily. She is mostly praise-driven, but a combination of praise and treat works best. She prefers to go to the bathroom off the leash so a fenced in yard would be ideal. 

I've made my way north in search of my new family. Is that with you? If so apply today! I won't be available for long! 

This dog tested positive for heartworm disease before arriving to the rescue. Heartworm disease is transmitted to a dog through a bite from an infected mosquito producing a positive test in six months. OPH will treat the dog and provide two weeks of recovery time prior to adoption. Potential adopters will receive detailed information on the disease and their role in completing the recovery process from OPHs heartworm coordinator. With monthly preventatives, the disease is completely preventable. 
Read more about heartworm disease here here
To adopt this dog, or any OPH dog, fill out the simple online application at https://ophrescue.org 
Operation Paws for Homes, Inc. (OPH) rescues dogs of all breeds and ages from high-kill shelters in NC, VA, MD, and SC, reducing the numbers being euthanized. With limited resources, the shelters are forced to put down 50-90% of the animals that come in the front door. OPH provides pet adoption services to families located in VA, DC, MD, PA and neighboring states. OPH is a 501(c)(3) organization and is 100% donor funded. OPH does not operate a shelter or have a physical location. We rely on foster families who open their homes to give love and attention to each dog before finding a forever home.

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Annie (TX) is a female Shepherd mix rescued in Texas. Our veterinary partner estimates that Annie is 7 months old at the time of intake in January 2021. Annie is good with people and other dogs, but cats are not her friends! It's hard to believe the level of cruelty that exists in the world, but it smacked us in the face when we saw the condition this poor pup was in when she was surrendered to a kill shelter by her owner, the person Annie trusted to love and take care of her. Annie was just skin and bones, weak and sick at less than half the weight she should be. She did not get into that condition overnight. Annie has been treated by our veterinary partner and she is on the road to recovery. Annie is a spunky pup who can't wait to explore all the world has to offer her--and that's much more than she has ever had. If you can give Annie a happy life that far exceeds the quality of life being led by her disgusting abuser, please apply online to adopt Annie (TX) at www.rescuedogsrocknyc.org.
