Dogs will be brought into the outdoor kennel for you to meet and make your decision. MASKS WILL BE MANDATORY to maintain EVERYONE'S safety  NO EXCEPTIONS PLEASE !! Unless otherwise noted, the puppies and dogs listed will arrive on Saturday, January 23rd 2021 .
Please follow this link to fill out an application. It is step one in adopting a pup from our rescue.
http://littlerhodyrescue.com/adoption-application/ 
 

*Filling an application does not guarantee you as the adopter. All applicant's references will be called. PLEASE call your veterinarian and personal references and allow consent to speaking with us ! 
We cannot process your application otherwise. Failure will put your application in 'Limbo"  
We process applications as they arrive. The first approved applicant will be called and the pup taken off of Petfinder. We do not have the man/ woman power to all all other applicants to advise them. 
IF there s another dog that you are interested in as well, please list at the top of the application and we will enter your application for that pup if the first choice has been adopted. 

THANK YOU !!! You are giving a first rate dog a second chance....By adopting! 

***** SADLY , we need to put this in print: THIS IS A RESCUE DOG. We do NOT know their birthday / age.  (unless other wise noted)  
More often than not, OUR TEAM  has saved them from euthanasia in Southern shelters. 
We do not know any more than our Veterinarians offer to us. 
 We often have them in kennels, and utilize crate training.  House training status is often NOT KNOWN. 
Prior Health, estimated weight  (as an adult), breed (Including the parents' breed , size or mix)   and some health concerns are  NOT KNOWN unless our veterinarians discover it and offer the information to us.   Again, these are strays and turn ins from all over the country. They do NOT come with labels; nor guarantees. 

Characteristics and disposition can and will evolve with time.
YOU the adopter are responsible to train and keep up to date on vaccines and preventatives.  
YOU the adopter are responsible for taking care of this new member of your family. 
 *************

****
Our adoption fees are $ 600. This fee includes the transportation of the pet from one of the organizations that we work with in TX, LA or TN. Before joining us in RI all dogs are: spayed/neutered, microchipped, up to date on age-appropriate vaccines, and on de-wormers, flea/tick and heartworm prevention. In addition, all adults (6 months +) are heartworm tested and MUST be negative for both heartworm and microfilaria before transport. 

In addition to the above, all dogs must have a Certificate of Veterinary Inspection and be deemed healthy per USDA law in order to travel. Once they have been certified they are then transported via USDA transport services only, which is required by law. 
 We  sometimes don't understand how bad the situation is for these pups and dogs in southern states.  Many people in the south don't spay or neuter their pets as we do here. Subsequently, there are thousands of beautiful , worthy pups and dogs, kittens and cats  that are dumped, shot, abandoned, brought into shelters, neglected, abused and abandoned.  We step in , tend to their veterinary needs. As you can see above, we never fail to properly spay and neuter. Everything is done with the  caring , capable hands of our veterinarians to get them healthy and ready to place them for adoption. That's when we put the demand for family- friendly pets with the supply ..... 

Give a first rate dog a second chance!!!! ADOPT! 


Keep in mind that we also offer a two week return policy for the return of a healthy dog that includes a full refund. We want to make sure that the adoption is a perfect fit for both you and the dog.

If you would like more information about adopting please select "More About Little Rhody Rescue" where you will also find our online application if you'd like to proceed with the adoption process. Thank you!

If you have an interest in a particular BACS animal, please email KSwanson@cityofberkeley.info. Following that, if you feel like it could be a good adoption fit, shelter staff will help coordinate a socially-distanced meeting in person so that you can meet your potential family member up-close and personal. Thank you for your patience during this time. We really appreciate your support!

Carden is a sweet, lovable middle-aged dog. He is kind of like a big teddy bear. He just wants to snuggle, go on walks, and play with his toys all day. He is very friendly when meeting new people and other dogs, and has done great living alongside our other Shepherd. He can be skittish sometimes because he is inexperienced with the world, but we don't consider him a fundamentally "anxious" dog. He crates well overnight and when needed during the day, and has done a great job learning leash manners and basic commands. Now all he needs is a loving forever home!

Meet Brandy! She is a goofy, fun loving, ball of fluff! She loves to play with toys (no stuffed ones) and people! She is crate and house trained. She still has some puppy energy as she is still young being around 1.5-2 years old. We are working on manners and obedience (so far we know sit really well and working on laying down and waiting). Please e-mail us for more information or go to our website https://soardogs.org/adoption-application for an application. Thank you very much! 


All SOAR dogs go through a ten-day quarantine period to ensure they are healthy, before being adopted. We do not operate on a first come first serve basis, but screen applicants in order to find the best fit for our adoptable dogs.

**If you are interested in adopting one of the puppies, please download and fill out an application from our website www.forgottendogsrescue.com. The puppies' adoption fee is $450, and they will come to their adopters spayed/neutered, microchipped, with age appropriate vaccinations, and several dewormings.** 

Biscotti is very outgoing, confident, active and playful (he's a very rough and tumble physical player). He would do best in a home with an adult dog to help guide him, and with an adopter who will keep up with training to ensure Biscotti grows up to be the best dog possible.

We are now accepting applications for our 20 puppies, the cookie and spice litters!

See more photos of all of the puppies on their Facebook album: 
https://www.facebook.com/media/set?vanity=forgottendogsrescue&set=a.3921486117870156

In November, we were contacted by our partners at Yakima Valley Pet Rescue (YVPR) to help with these litters of puppies. YVPR had taken in two pregnant moms (who were both in the same household) and were able to get them into one of their foster homes where the puppies were then born.  Unfortunately, the owners of the mom dogs only agreed to let YVPR (and, subsequently, us) take the puppies under the condition that the moms get returned to them but YVPR is going to ensure the moms spayed so they don’t have to go through this again. We would love to take the mom dogs as well but, this is out of our control and we are happy to, at least, help their puppies. 

As with most of our pups, we aren’t sure of their mixes but the moms appear to be part Pit Bull type dogs.  They are not related but, we think the puppies may all have had the same dad as there was a Pit Bull roaming around the area and the puppies were born within a day of each other.  Of course, this is all conjecture.  

The Cookie litter (9 puppies) were born on 10/30 and the Spice Litter (11 puppies) were born on 10/31. 

Cookie Litter:
Chocolate Chip - Male
Macaroon - Male
Samoa - Male
Biscotti - Male
Gingersnap - Female
No-Bake - Male
Rum Ball - Male
Macadamia - Male
Molasses - Female

Spice Litter:
Ginger - Female
Nutmeg - Female
Pepper - Male
Cocoa - Female
Cinnamon - Female
Caper - Male
Poppy - Female
Clove - Female
Dill - Male
Chipotle - Male
Juniper - Female

The pups have all been in loving foster homes in groups of 2 and 3 for the last month, and have been socialized, exposed to lots of new things, and have started working on house and crate training.  Several have been with kids or kitties or adult dogs or all of these or some of these. We will be working closely with each approved applicant to determine the best fit for the adoptive puppy and the family based on what we know about their personalities and temperaments. 


Please note that due to a large influx of applications we get for puppies, it can take several weeks for us to finish reviewing and processing them to find the best match for each individual puppy. Once adoption applications are approved, meetings will be set up with approved applicants, and, as mentioned, more information on individual puppies’ temperaments will be given and we will be working with each applicant to determine the best fit for the puppy and their prospective family.

animal.description:
Penny is an adorable pom-mix (she does not shed) who just wants to please and doesn’t require anything more than love. She will be a wonderful addition to any family who has lots of love to spare. She likes to lie in her bed as long as she knows you are close by. If she has a little mat in the kitchen she will lay there and nap while you cook. She will get up and follow you every time you go anywhere. She loves to go on car rides and take walks as long as it’s relatively flat. She is very much a lap dog and likes to be carried. She loves her bed doesn’t mind wearing little outfits (that she looks adorable in).

Penny is very mellow. She is good on a leash, good with other dogs, crate and house trained.  She is not a barker. She has not been around cats but we don’t think she would care.  She is a little hard of hearing so you need to raise your voice to get her attention, or just make sure that she can see you.  Once she sees you she will follow you around.  She is a good eater – no left overs for her! She has not had any accidents in her foster home, but is given multiple opportunities to go outside throughout the day.  She sleeps in her crat but prefers the door left open.  We have not had her about kids but think she would do well in an adult home or home with older kids.  

Penny would do well with a family who stays home most of the time, and likes to take her on little trips out.  She would do best in a home with a woman (she is ok with men but prefers women). She enjoys her daily walks, and also travels well in a dog stroller.

Penny is in Yorba Linda CA, she is aged to be ~10 years old and weighs 8 ½ lbs.  She has some opacity in both eyes but is able to see. She is healthy, recently had a dental (jan 2021), is spayed, up to date on her vaccinations and micro chipped. If you are interested in adopting our little Miss Penny, adoption applications are available at http://bichonrescuebrigade.org/adopt/adoption-form

animal.description:
*** COURTESY POSTING ***  
Charlie’s true breed mix is unknown, but his happy go lucky, eager to please attitude pretty much makes him a unicorn, so we will go with that!  
 He is looking for a new home due to no fault of his own.  His family is having living arrangement issues.   He is located in Waco.   He loves every human he meets, is dog neutral when working, will do absolutely anything for even the smallest piece of kibble, and does enjoy a good game of tug. He is a high energy guy who loves to work, but he also has a great off switch when crated or just hanging out. He’s previously lived with small dogs and children, and is reported to have done well with them, but was a bit of a bull in a China shop. Never aggressive, just overly enthusiastic. He’s completed a 28 day board and train and knows sit, down, loose leash heeling, place, doorway manners, crate manners, and even some foundation agility work! He will climb on, jump over, and balance on anything! He could excel as a demo dog, trick dog, or agility dog. He also did well out hiking, and politely passed by other hikers. He was more interested in other dogs in that setting, but was easily redirected and reminded to focus. I can’t think of many negatives about this guy, other than maybe the fact that he slobbers a lot when working for treats, lol! He also turns into a bit of a boy when outdoors, and likes to put his nose to the ground and jet off to sniff and pee. However, if kept engaged and working, he won’t disconnect in that way. He’s truly a joy to work with and brings enthusiasm to everything he does. He learns very quickly and is highly motivated!

Fast facts:
- Neutered male, fully up to date on all vaccinations and veterinary care, and healthy
- Located in Waco, TX
- High food drive, medium toy drive
- Very dog neutral and tolerant in a training setting
- Loves people
- Smart, high energy, easily trainable
- Just turned 5 years old

animal.description:
HASHBROWN & WAFFLES NEED A FOSTER OR LOVING FOREVER HOME!!!
Fosters make it possible for Dogs XL to save and care for homeless and abandoned dogs! To learn about fostering dogs like Hashbrown & Waffles, please contact us at http://www.dogsxlrescue.org/volunteer/foster

Names: Hashbrown & Waffles

Breed: Great Pyrenees

Approximate Age: 4 years old 

Approximate Weight: each of them is ~80 lbs but Hashbrown is taller and thinner where Waffles is shorter and stockier

Currently Living at: Local Foster Home

 

 
Do you need more floof in your life? Adopt a pyr or TWO! Hashbrown (lighter and taller) and Waffles darker and shorter) are a bonded pair of 4 year old male, neutered Great Pyrenees mixes looking for a forever family! 

 
 

 
These two are the definition of a bonded pair and we will not separate them. They must be within three inches of each other AT ALL TIMES - no ifs, ands, or buts about it. Sometimes they almost pee on each other when one marks a bush (or a scooter, or a tree, or a pole, or a bike, or a car tire) and the other just has to see what’s going on. Alas, being attached at the hip has its benefits and its trials.  

 
 

 
Hashbrown and Waffles lived their first four years as outdoor dogs, but found themselves at a shelter for killing chickens instead of guarding them... oops. 

 
 

 
Because they spent so long as outside dogs, they are still learning their house manners and are specifically working on house training. They like to mark things... even piles of clean laundry, but they’ve come a long way towards learning that inside is not a bathroom and with frequent potty breaks, they’re doing very well! We expect some regression in a new home, so keep a stash of Nature’s Miracle on hand ;) 

 
 

 
The Breakfast Boys (TM) have good leash manners and won’t pull you in opposite directions since, ya know, they’re attached at the hip, but they do like to chase squirrels so beware they hunt as a pair, and although they’ll enjoy occasional strolls, they’re looking for a family with a fenced in yard so they can wrestle with each other to their hearts’ content. Typical pyrs, these two aren’t exactly quiet either, but unlike your average GP, Hashbrown and Waffles ARE quite trainable! Just make sure you have good treats on hand or they’re not interested. 

 
 

 
The Breakfast Club has welcomed other canine members with open paws, but would be perfectly happy to be your two and only as well! They can be a little too eager about small animals, and given their history, we would not recommend a home with cats. 

 
 

 
Hashbrown and Waffles are incredibly friendly, loving and affectionate with people, but are just as happy to occupy themselves with a toy or take a nap in the same room as their people if you’re busy. Pyrs might shed and double the pyr means double the floof but you can always use their fur to knit a blanket to keep you warm this winter! The Breakfast Boys are total love bugs and they’re worth every bit of mischief they may cause.

 
 

 
Hashbrown and Waffles are looking for a forever home who will welcome them both (we will not separate them).

 
 

Hashbrown & Waffles need a foster or a loving forever home to lavish love and attention on them. Please open your heart and home to "DOG NAME"!


The adoption fee for this pair is $600, which includes the cost of heartworm treatment and routine vetting, including vaccinations and spay/neuter.

 

If you are interested in adopting, please fill out the application online at http://www.dogsxlrescue.org/adopt/adoption-questionnaire

 

Thank you for considering adoption and helping to save a life!
 

Please visit us online at www.DogsXLRescue.org

Incredibly sweet, affectionate and gentle, Fawn is looking to find a person who she can give all her love to. Like so many lovebug pitbulls, Fawn thinks she's a lap dog and will happily climb aboard to sit on your lap for kisses and cuddles. She loves a good belly scratch and will let you know if you stop too soon!

Dainty and easy to walk, Fawn enjoys to go for walks to sniff the flowers and see what's going on in the neighborhood. Although she's low energy around the house, she will happily go for short runs or hikes. She is friendly to all new people she meets, and not really interested other dogs.

Quiet and mellow in the house, Fawn will only bark to alert you if there's someone outside the house or the UPS truck is making their deliveries on your street.

She loves treats, and will shake your hand to say thank you!

Fawn is a very loving and mellow dog, and will make someone such a wonderful loyal and loving companion. She is calm and very sweet around children, and just an overall gem of a dog. We are all a little bit in love with this beautiful and kind natured senior lady.

Fawn is 9 years old, 65 lbs, and ready for her forever home! Please visit www.liveloveanimalrescue.org to fill out an adoption application.

animal.description:
Meet Raddix! 

Raddix is estimated to be 1 years old and 15lbs. Raddix arrived in Wisconsin after being surrendered with his litter mates.  Since he has lived his entire life with his siblings, Raddix is learning how to be independently confident.  Raddix is a very sweet but shy boy who will need a home that is willing to be patient with him. Once he comes out of his shell, Raddix loves attention and he loves to play.  Raddix is doing very well with learning how to share and process stimuli.  His foster feels he will be a great dog to go hiking with or walking on the trails.  It will take time to get him confident enough to that point but this boy is well worth the patience. Raddix is beyond sweet.  He loves to give kisses and loves turning over for belly rubs.  He is very interested in children and wags his tail when he sees them.  Since he is still working on his confidence, he will need a home without young children for now. Raddix would do well with another confident dog in the house.  Raddix is very quiet when he is left alone but when it comes to sleep time he wants to share your bed! 

Interested in this sweet dog? Apply today at http://www.underdogpetrescue.org/dog-application

**Please note: Our animals live in foster homes throughout the Madison area. We do not have a shelter where animals are available for daily viewing. Applying is the first step in our process.**

Dogs from Underdog Pet Rescue come with the following medical care already provided:
Spay/Neuter
Rabies, Distemper, and Bordetella Vaccinations (as age appropriate-puppy adopters may need to cover some vaccine boosters)
Heartworm Test (for dogs over 6mo)
Microchip
Deworming
Heartworm and Flea/Tick Preventative
Any other necessary medical treatment as recommended by veterinarian

Our adult dog adoption fee is $300. Our puppy (under 5 mo) is $375. Our senior dog (over 8 yrs) is $250.

animal.description:
A Good Samaritan scooped Ripley up off the side of the road as his foot left a trail of bloody paw prints and he staggered from side to side; the chainlink catching the sun with each step. They brought sweet Ripley to the Texas Shelter. Staff prepared the bolt cutters as they went to remove the piece of chain that was embedded so deeply into Ripley's neck it required sedation. His toe is fractured and buckshot litters his head and skull. Ripley was a target in someone's sick game. 

Ripley was networked immediately and his story went unnoticed. The sea of dogs in need engulfed his plea. No one stepped up and no one was able to help. And then we were contacted here at 4P4L. We will have Ripley transported into our care the week of Jan 13th and hope to have a family waiting.

He seems fearful of other dogs at this time, though with decompression and love, that could change.

HW+ simply means the dog has tested positive for heart worms in our screening process. We utilize what is called the fast-kill method which means we place the dog on antibiotics for 30 days and then administer 3 injections in increments afterward. The cost to treat heart worms is rather steep. However, thanks to our generous donors, we are able to cover that cost for our adopters so long as they go to our veterinarian, Red Rocks Animal Center in Lakewood.

We have no back story or update for this dog at this time. When we do, it will be updated here. This is all the information we have currently.


	Approved Applicants may make the adoption fee payment by clicking donate above. Partial adoption fees will not hold a dog.
	Dogs adopted with our rescue come with FREE training from #GoodPup to help you build strong bonds from the start!
	If upon meeting the dog of your choosing at an adoption event you find that you aren't a good match, your deposit will be refunded minus a 10% administration fee.
	Adoption fees include vaccines up until time of adoption, microchip, spay/neuter and 1st 30 days of free Pet insurance. We are not affiliated with Pet First pet insurance. (you have to sign up for the insurance or it will not go into effect). 
	Adopters can go to our vet for medical issues that may arise in 1st 3 days of adoption. 
	The dogs in our care are fostered in Colorado, Texas, and New Mexico. While all dogs are picked up during our scheduled times, sometimes transport dates change due to unforeseen circumstances.
animal.name: Ripley HW+

animal.description:
Capo is estimated to be somewhere between 5-7 yrs old. His paperwork says 7 but he displays a slightly younger personality and energy. He is very eager to please people, smart and ready to learn, takes corrections well and responds better to affection/attention reward faster than he does food reward with the exception of the mastiff butt-plant when he doesn't want to go somewhere. He is doing very well with training and acclimations to an inside the home environment. He's an absolute love who needs someone to show him who the leader is, leep him challenged intellectually and physically. 

He needs the confidence and trust in his human, built from consistency and positive interaction/direction/redirection to make him his best pupper. As a slightly insecure dog, he does become overstimulated easliy. His anxiety response is to mount, hump or chew. The chewing presents more if the attention is withdrawn but he can still see the person he wants attention. Because of his humping and mouthing behaviors and easliy overstimulated, he is not recommended for any family with rambunctious play atmosphere or small children. He would be best with the only dog. He exhibits interest in playing with cats but no aggression or prey drive. He does really well with cats. We prefer Capo be an only dog, however he ok around other calm dogs. He will resource guard for attention (not toys or food), so when other dogs get attention, Capo will react. So, he needs a home that is familiar with this insecure behavior, will continue to crate him (it's his safe place and used for downtime), and will be consistent with Capo. Like most dogs, Capo wants your direction, he strives to make his person happy and is a very smart boy. He can be mouthy when he wants affection or play time with you. While he is gently about being mouthy, we are working on redirecting this behavior and would like a family that would continue to do the same for him. 

He is not neutered yet due to a skin infection that has to heal first. Once healed the infection is not expected to be a reoccurring issue. He is up to date on vaccinations and on monthly heartworm and flea prevention. In the few weeks Capo has been with his foster, he has been learning, adjusting, and seeking a human bond. We hope to find him the perfect family he can begin to build this bond with. He is a very good boy who needs his fur-ever family with a calmer home to help him relax, continue to build confidence, and will take him on walks.

animal.description:
If you are interested in adopting Ritz, please email anna.hidalgo@gmail.com.

Do you have room in your heart, and your lap, for a handsome young guy? Ritz is a friendly, playful pup who will greet you with tail wags and a gentle lean in for the good scratches! If given the green light, he will happily land in your lap for a proper snuggle. Ritz waits patiently to get ready for walks and will happily lead the way. 

Ritz has been described as a "dream in the home" and already knows a handful of commands like "sit", "down", and "leave it". He is highly treat motivated, loves to play, and always looks forward to learning new tricks. He is very eager to take part in all family activities and truly sticks to his favorite people like glue. He will be a great addition to an active, adult-only family that can take him on several long walks a day and continue to work on his obedience training and leash manners. Ritz prefers the serenity of rural life as the sights and sounds of the city can be overwhelming for him. He would love to find an experienced and confident family that will help him feel safe and stay calm around big vehicles, loud noises, and other dogs. Ritz can be picky when it comes to dogs so he prefers to be the only dog in the home so he can soak up all the attention and treats you have to offer. While Ritz is small in stature, he is big on needing plenty of space, so an apartment or small condo would not be his ideal living environment. His dream home is one with a fenced yard with grass as far as the eye can see for him to play fetch and explore the outdoors. Ritz is looking forward to finding his forever home so come meet him today! 

Estimated DOB: 11/13/19

animal.description:
Hello friends my name is Snoop and I am a 14 month old chi/mix! I arrived on Jan 17th to Wisconsin to find my forever family! When I went to my foster home it was amazing, there were all these people and dogs I met and did so good with them. I get so happy when I see people that I can’t stop wiggling. I have very long legs so when I walk I have like a little dance step in me. I have done so good that my foster dad took me to see my foster mom at work and boy did I love that place because everyone I met had treats for me!! So to my forever family out there.....I love car rides, walks, cuddling, most of all I love seeing people! Oh and treats I love, love, love treats!

If you would like to be considered as a potential adopter for one of our great dogs, please go to our website- www.luckymuttsrescue.org and submit an application. Our application process includes landlord approval and vet checks. Please make sure all of your information is current and accurate, including a valid email address and phone numbers. Inaccuracies and/or incomplete data will delay and/or cancel your application.  We strive to process all applications in a timely manner, but with the high volume of applications we are receiving, it is taking anywhere from 1-3 weeks.  You may be contacted via email if there are concerns or questions.  Once all of your information is reviewed and if your application is approved, you will be notified via email.  Submitting an application and receiving an approval does not guarantee you will be adopting the dog you applied for.  Once you move to the meet and greet process, you will be contacted by the foster family to further discuss the dog, and answer questions you may have, and if applicable, a meet and greet will be set up at our adoption center.   Meet and greets are only set up with approved applicants, and we require all members in the household to be present, as well as any current dogs in the home. 

Current Adoption Fees Are:
$400+tax for puppies to 3 years old
$350+tax for ages 4-7
$250+tax for ages 8 and up
Bonded pairs vary

The adoption fee covers spay/neuter, up to date age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, general deworming, heartworm test, (if over 6  months) and a certified veterinary inspection. Please be aware, listed dog breeds are based on information provided and cannot be guaranteed.  Submitting an application for a particular dog does not guarantee that you will be the applicant chosen, we receive several applications for each dog. Our adopters are picked based on the needs of the dog, and the home we feel with best fit based on your responses to our application, vet information and landlord requirements.   Approved applicants not chosen for the dog you applied for, will be in active status for a period of six months.  We encourage you to watch Petfinder, Facebook and our website for upcoming dogs.  Should you see a dog that interests you, please send us a Facebook message or an email with your approval number.  Please be patient with us, as Lucky Mutts Rescue is run strictly by volunteers and many of us work full time jobs, have families and also foster dogs. Thank you for considering Lucky Mutts Rescue for your next furry family member!

LILY is a young 2yr old sweet girl who was surrendered to a shelter as she does have a 5/6 heart issue which is controlled by daily medication. We have had her to the cardiologist twice and she seems to be doing well.
She loves to go on  walks but obviously only moderate exercise for her!
Unfortunately due to her heart issue which she was born with we have been advised by the vet not to spay her as putting her under general anesthesia is dangerous.
The cardiologist  diagnosed a heart valve issue.  Her medication is not terribly expensive, around $25 per month.  We have been told she will be fine as she tolerates the medication very well and just needs to have a vet check up every 6 months by her primary  vet. Cardiologist is not necessary.
She was fine for the groomer recently. She would enjoy a home with at least 1 person home most of the time.
If you are interested in adopting sweet LILY please go to our website www.somersetcottagepoodlerescue.org and click on adopt to download the application

animal.description:
**Please read Major's entire profile, which includes a link to the adoption application. Thank you!** 

Meet Major, a one year old, 48 pound, Labrador/Heeler mix young fellow.

Major's first family down south took him to the vet for a check-up and never came back. It's hard to understand how they could have parted from such a sweet, handsome boy.

A loving young dog that loves to follow his humans around, Major's very playful and active. He enjoys going on runs. He needs an active family that will get him plenty of exercise and include him in their adventures, and a fence would be ideal. (He is not suited to an apartment setting.)

Major's very smart and learns quickly. He is working with his foster and has already learned lie down, come, and stay. He is still working on sit! He is getting better and better on a leash. He is also house and crate trained, and sleeps through the night in his crate. He's still a puppy in many ways, and needs a family that will continue his training.

He loves everyone he meets and gets along great with other dogs. Major thinks children are the best friends ever and is very gentle with them. However, he has shown some signs of resource guarding with high value items like bones. With that and his energy level we recommend a family with teens and above.

Major tested positive for Heartworm once he came north and his treatment is in process. The cost of treatment will be covered by Great Dog Rescue at our veterinarian. However, his furever family has to be committed to getting him to his appointments.

A world class snuggler and cuddler, Major loves attention and follows his humans around - he's already a great companion and will continue to blossom with his furever family.

All dogs are up to date on vaccinations and spayed/neutered at the time of adoption.  All dogs require professional training to become the best family member they can be.

To adopt or learn more about Major, you must fill out an adoption application. To find the application, copy and paste this URL into your browser: WWW.GDRNE.COM/ADOPTION-APPLICATION [Adoption Fee: $495]  **  PLEASE READ: If a dog is listed, then s/he is currently available for adoption. Their information is correct to the best of our abilities and the information we have been given as of the day of posting. Please note, GDRNE does not guarantee the breed of any dog or puppy unless stated that we have run DNA. All breeds listed are educated estimates. Our dogs are rescued from various situations. It is most likely that both their parents were strays and even if not, mixes of some sort and that their grandparents were mixes as well. The dog may have some genetic material of an American Staffordshire Terrier (pit bull). The dogs are usually mixes of many breeds, making them a breed all their own - a True and adorable American MUTT. If you are interested in this dog, you must submit an application. Great Dog is not a shelter so there is no building you can visit. Our dogs live in private foster homes until adopted. To learn more about our *shelterless* rescue, adoption fees, and procedures, review the list of Frequently Asked Questions on our website at WWW.GDRNE.COM.

animal.description: Hello, my name is Harley! I'm only a year old, but I've been through a lot. I came to Wisconsin all the way from Texas with my 6 newborn puppies - and now that they've all gotten big and been adopted I'm looking for a furever home of my own. I'm a very sweet dog but I can get really anxious in new situations or meeting new people, so I'll need a family that's pretty dog-savvy or ready to learn a lot about canine body language. I think I would get pretty overwhelmed by the exciting antics of young children, so would prefer a home of teenagers and/or adults. I'm very intelligent and respond quickly to positive reinforcement, and I have been learning all sorts of skills at the shelter; I'm excited to learn even more in a home. I spent some time in a foster home and they said I'm really good about housetraining and crate training. I am a little particular about my dog friends, but like playing with compatible pups so if you have an energetic and social dog we might be a great team! If you think you are a good fit for a girl like me, contact the shelter today!

animal.description:
Our southern belle, "Delta Dawn", has completed her time in foster care and is headed to the farm to find a furever family of her own. Delta is a middle aged hound girl and weighs about 65 lbs. It was very clear to her foster mom that Delta had never experienced any of the finer things in life that a dog would love such as a warm house to relax the days away, a loving family to keep her safe, and dog friends to play with. She is slowly, but surely warming up to the idea of being a furry family member and has made great strides since joining her foster family a couple months ago. She can now walk on a leash, where before she had no clue what that long rope attached to her collar was, and loves to go exploring and follow her hound nose to all the wonderful smells along the way. When she is in a fenced yard, she loves to get any zoomies out by running the yard a few times. She has also mastered the "sit" Command and even offers a little paw up while sitting, which she threw in all by herself for extra cuteness. She's very treat motivated and with a little work she's sure to master any other skills you may want her to possess. Delta has fallen in love with all people she's come in contact with and has learned the humans mean her no harm and just want to enjoy her company. She loves to come over for head scratches and ear rubs. She enjoyed the kids in her foster home, but would probably do best in a home with older kids. Delta does get nervous when it comes to loud noises or chaos, but we're sure that would only get better with time as she's more comfortable in her new home. She would like to request that her new family give her the time and patience to warm up to her new environment, but once she does, she has a lot of love to give and is truly a super super sweet gal that will offer years of companionship.

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description:
Raven is a 6 yr old female chihuahua mix that weighs about 10 lbs.  She is very sweet but super shy. She will take several days to a week to warm up to new people but she is not aggressive at all.

She came from a person who was a hoarder and had over 50 dogs in a small trailer. She loves the company of dogs over people. She has been in our rescue now for a little over 1 yr because it’s taken her that long to learn to trust. She used to run and hide and now she enjoys coming out sitting in your lap for pets. 

She loves to be around other dogs so she would be best in a home with another dog.  She does have skin allergies and needs an allergy shot once a month, if not she’ll continue to scratch and her fur will fall out. 

She is house trained and can now walk on a leash. Raven needs someone that will be patient with her.  Her foster has a puppy and she enjoys playing with him. She doesn’t care much for toys. Not good with small children only because she is so shy. So best in a home with kids 12 yrs and up.  

If you are interested in Raven, please complete the on-line application or contact us for more information.

animal.description:
APPLY at Heartsforpawsrescue.com/adoption-application
heartsforpawsrescue.com/adopt

MEET MACARONI — Spayed, Vaccinated, chipped, 8 month Shepherd/Pit Female 60 lbs. Owner Surrender originally adopted from the Valley Oak SPCA.

Why is the dog being given up?: Moving into a new house that does not allow dogs

Check the words that best describe your dog.: FRIENDLY, NOISY, ACTIVE, PLAYFUL, SMART, AFFECTIONATE, OBEDIENT, ROUGH

Is your dog housebroken?: Yes

Does the dog get along with:: Dog-Friendly. She has lived with two other dogs both big and small, she gets along well with both sizes. She has been to the dog park but will usually only sit on the bench meant for people and watch the others. She will play with dogs that are isolated rather than in a group, she also gets scared when dogs at the park bark at her she doesn’t realize that they just want to play.

Does your dog have handling sensitivities? How is your dog meeting strangers?: She loves strangers or any attention from anyone

Where does the dog sleep?: She has her own bed

Is the dog allowed on your furniture?: Yes

Is the dog crate trained?: No

Where do you keep your dog: Outside to play and use the restroom then inside whenever she comes to the door

How does the dog react to being left alone?: Cries if she’s alone for a long period of time and doesn’t see anyone or barks, but for the most part she doesn’t mind being alone as long as she sees you every now and then

Please list any particular fears your dog has.: Doesn’t like fireworks or other dogs that are too aggressive with her

Does the dog have any known health problems?: No

Does the dog like riding in the car?: Yes

What is the dog's favorite :Bones, Walking, swimming for small periods of time, smelling everythingShe loves food, we give her blueberries, carrots, coconut oil, peanut butter(organic), boiled chicken, pumpkin all in moderation she loves it

Is there anything else you can share that is special, unusual, or endearing about your dog that will help the new owners?: She will only dig to hide her bones or toys, even food if she gets full at times so we don’t allow her to have toys outside unless we watch her. She will hide her bones around the house, usually in her bed but sometimes behind couch cushions or blankets

Are there any things you think a new owner needs to know?: Do not leave her around trash 

Please provide a summary of the “ideal” home for your dog:: A home with another dog for her to play with, our chihuahua is her best friend so even a small dog will work. She loves attention so someone that has a lot of time on their hands and doesn’t mind how talkative she is. She likes to play but walks aren’t usually her favorite because she gets tired fast so other dogs are a good way for her to let out some energy. She is very affectionate but likes to have her own space to sleep and hide her bones, she will purposely isolate herself when she wants to sleep or needs space. No cats.

$300 adoption donation.

APPLY at Heartsforpawsrescue.com/adoption-application

animal.description:
Meet Spud!
Spud was a victim of a massive hoarding case in Atlanta. He was seized along with almost 50 other dogs and his past "owners" are facing charges! Spud lived in a very small space in his own urine and feces. He likely NEVER got outside and because of that he’s very overweight at 125lbs. He needs to lose 15-20lbs.  He also has a few other health issues we will manage.

Spud is sweet, smart, smiley guy who has risen above the circumstances he found himself in due to human neglect. He has proven that at the shelter when he was first seized, the staff fell in love with him! I mean look at that smile!

Spud is excellent with other dogs and has no issue with cats! Given his large size, we recommend kids 12+!

Spud is in a medical foster for now to jump-start his diet and exercise routine. He will be available for adoption in 3-4weeks (1/8/2020).  However, we are beginning to take applications. 

If you are interested in adopting Spud, please apply at www.twotailzrescue.org!

Please email info@prairiepaws.org to fill out an application and arrange an appointment to meet the pet. Want to get a head start on the application? Here's the link: DOG ADOPTION APPLICATION: https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/adopt/PPAS/Dog

Atlas is a happy go lucky male shepherd mix with an estimated DOB of 08/12/2017. He weighed 63.6 lbs at intake.  Atlas came to us as a transfer from another shelter.  Atlas loves to romp around in the play yard and when he is done running about he loves to cuddle and bury his head in your lap. He loves to play with another dog that likes to play to the max. Ready to give this sweet boy a wonderful new home? His adoption fee is $190 which includes a medical exam, sterilization surgery, age-appropriate vaccinations, dewormer, heartworm testing, and a microchip.

Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable so for most of the dogs we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. As we get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.

Our animals change daily, so please check our lists of adoptable dogs and adoptable cats frequently. Once you find an animal you’d like to adopt, the next steps are to complete an application and request a meet and greet with the foster. Make sure to be thorough and help us understand why you’re interested in that particular animal — and why your home is a great fit. Based on your answers we may even have a better fit for you.

All PPAS dogs are up to date on all of their vaccines (including rabies if age appropriate), and will be microchipped and registered in the adopter's name at the time of adoption. Adopters get a free consultation at an area vet partner within 14 days of adoption. Any dog that is six months of age or older will be tested for Heartworms and if found negative, will be kept on Heartworm prevention during their shelter stay, after the adoption it is up to the adopter to continue the highly recommended Heartworm preventative treatment. Also all PPAS shelter dogs are treated with a monthly topical flea/tick preventative and we ask that adopters continue that treatment as well.  All dogs and cats per state law are sterilized before they begin their new fabulous lives with their new families.

Adoption fees: Adoption fees must be paid in full at time of adoption – no partial payments are accepted. All major credit cards are accepted. Adoption fees vary. Please note if you live in the city of Ottawa a dog license fee must also be paid at time of adoption. Annual renewal of dog licenses is required between January 1st and February 15th.

Taking your animal home: The State of Kansas requires that all cats and dogs must be sterilized (spayed/neutered) before going to their new homes. In most cases animals will have already been sterilized before being placed on the adoption floor and you will be able to take your new companion home with you the day of adoption. However, if the animal is not yet sterilized, they will need to stay at the shelter and we will schedule the surgery on the next available date (usually within a week). We do request that all dogs go home with a collar/leash.

If you are interested in this pet, please either email Prairie Paws Animal Shelter at info@prairiepaws.org, for an application or visit our website @ prairiepaws.org for more information.

Th human that he loved, opened the car door, pushed him out of the vehicle and kept driving. Dante chased after the car and out of sight. Due to flight limitations, we are only able to ship to our two adoption partners safely, upper East Coast and Minnesota. Dante is fully vetted, sterilized and ready to find his forever home. animal.description:
Hi! My official name is Ginger Snap, but folks just call me Ginger. We think I am a Beagle mix about 2-3 years old. They do not know much about my past except that I was not taken care of very well. I was tied up in someone's back yard and pretty much ignored. When the food ran out, they just stopped feeding me. I finally managed to break loose and was wandering around the neighborhood when I walked out in front of a car. Imagine my surprise when it turned out to be a wonderful couple that works with a dog rescue. They brought me in to the rescue, got me all cleaned up and gave me plenty of food and a warm place to sleep each night. At first, I did not know how to play with the other dogs, but they soon showed me the ropes and now we get along great! I love playing outside with the other dogs but then I like to come inside for some snuggle time and sit on the couch with my foster daddy and get some belly rubs! I need a home with a fenced yard where I can run and play, and I would love someone to play with. I am still a little nervous with new people and places. But once I get to know you, I love everyone. I have been spayed and I am up to date on my shots. Unfortunately, I tested light positive for heartworms. The good news is the vet says I should be all clear very soon if I keep up my monthly treatments. Fortunately, the rescue will continue to provide my medicine until I am heartworm negative. Being in the house is still kinda new for me but I am doing my best to be a good girl. We are working on some crate training; I don't really care for it but they say it is necessary at times and it helps keep me out of trouble.

I am looking for a furever family that will be patient and understand that I am still young and trying to learn all the rules. I need guidance and understanding. I am going to make mistakes, but I need a loving family that will teach me the right things to do and still love me even when I mess up. In return I will be your loving and faithful companion for life!

If you are interested in giving Ginger Snap a forever home, please visit the link below to fill out an application! http://fureverafterrescue.org/adoption-application.html It is best to submit an application through a computer. We have experienced some problems when applications have been submitted using a mobile device. *When you submit the application, you are not obligated to adopt however it does reserve for you the opportunity to adopt that particular animal. We review them on a first come first served basis. If your application is approved, we will contact you and allow you the opportunity to adopt. If you choose not to adopt, we will contact the next approved applicant. If you have any questions or difficulties, please contact us and we will be glad to help!

animal.description:
Hollie is a 1.5 year old spayed female purebred German Shepherd. SHE IS A VERY SPECIAL GIRL! She was given up by her owners due because they were moving away and knew she needed special care. Hollie was vomiting and was suspected to have some kind of liver disease going on. After we rescued her, we immediately got started on diagnostics for Hollie. She received a full bloodwork panel and then went on to undergo a CT scan. Unfortunately, Hollie was diagnosed with a congenital portosystemic liver shunt, along with hundreds of smaller acquired shunting vessels. 

Hollie is not a candidate for surgery and will need to be managed on daily medications. This includes only feeding her a special diet (Hill's L/d liver care dry food), daily administration of Lactulose, Denamarin liver support supplements, and daily antibiotics. 

With good supportive care, Hollie is able to live a normal life. She is housebroken, crate trained, VERY SMART, and loves to spend time at the dog park. She is a very sweet, and LOYAL dog. Hollie does well with other dogs in the house as part of the pack, but would be fine being an only dog as well. Hollie's adoption fee is $350 and we are interested in serious applicants only that understand Hollie's condition and will be able to provide this girl with the support and care that she needs for the rest of her life. 

Foster home location: Maple Grove, MN

If you are interested in adopting, please go to our website at www.castawaypetrescue.org and fill out an adoption application. An adoption counselor will contact you. Please note that adoption counselors will only know of your interest if you submit an application. They do not see emails sent to the administration email account. The adoption counselor can answer your questions when they call after receiving your application. Please remember we are an all volunteer organization.

Minimum Adoption Donation is $350 (includes deworming, microchip with free registration, age appropriate vaccinations, spay and 30 days of health insurance). Any donation above the minimum is appreciated

Foster Home Location: Maple Grove, MN

Our organization uses 24PetWatch microchips, which include free registration into the 24PetWatch pet recovery service. For more information visit www.24petwatch.com or call

animal.description:
Applications now being accepted!! ENZO is a playful, mouthy presa canaria mastiff. He estimated at 4 by our vet. He can be slow to warm up, but then is fine with people. For this reason, he'd do better in a house without a lot of traffic in and out and new people to stress him. He's a mouthy player, meaning he always does best with a toy in his mouth to keep busy, and he needs heavy duty ones! He weighs in at an impressive 90 lbs. He's a gorgeous dog! He's not yet cat-tested. He has been ok with a larger male dog but didn’t like a smaller male in one home that tried him. He has had no issues With female dogs. A meet and greet with any current pets to ensure  compatibility is required. 

** Enzo also would really benefit from a fenced-in yard where he can exercise off some of his energy. His fosters (who don't have a fenced in yard) were taking him on multiple mile-plus walks per day, and he STILL had excess energy to burn.

Contact us for more details as we continue to get more information from our foster.

Adoption fee covers: all vetting to age (including deworming, deflea etc ), spay/neuter (to be done at 6-8 months of age if not already done and included in adoption fee,  free 30 days of pet insurance, 6 week obedience course (or reimbursement for positive-based classes), and lifetime support of rescue.

Please fill out an application here for consideration: Tinyurl.Com/appshdr

* During this COVID-19 crisis, we are essentially doing only virtual application processing and meetings are using social distancing practices. We will not have any open hours until further notice and doing meet and greets by appointment with the utmost caution for personal safety. We are not a shelter so there are NO DOGS AT THE SHOP unless we have open hours. All our dogs are in foster care and are available to be seen by appointment.

NOTE: If a dog is listed as Adoptable, he or she is still available at that time. Also, our adoption area is within a several hour radius of us in Rochester, NY (NOT including Canada - sorry!)

animal.description:
Feliz is an affectionate lap dog and loves one-on-one attention. Estimated to have been born 6/1/16, and weighing in at 11 lbs, she enjoys going for long walks and playing with her toys.

She is very protective when it comes to eating and will guard her food, so she needs to be separated from other pets while eating or receiving treats. She is potty trained and knows how to use a pee pad also.  She knows how to use a doggie door, but will need a high fenced yard since she has the ability of jumping right over shorter fences.

Feliz would do best in a home where she is the only Princess since she is very much an alpha dog, and a home without children since she can become possessive and protective of her human.

If you are looking for a loyal companion, please complete an application found at http://rescueachi.com/adoption-application/ and her foster family will give you a call so you can see if you and she would be the perfect fit.

animal.description:
Chase is 1 year old and weighs about 18 lbs.  Chase came into our rescue as an owner surrender from one of our vet's clients.  He was left with the client by a friend and he never came back to pick him up and they already had 3 dogs.  He is getting neutered on January 22, 2021 and will be available for adoption after that.  Chase has been very good at the foster's home and gets along with all the dogs and is fine with cats.  He goes outside to go potty but does wear a bellyband in the house.  He was never trained.  Once he is neutered and the testosterone leaves his system he more than likely with do much better.  Belly bands are wonderful for training male dogs.  He is very affectionate and loves attention.  He also loves to play with other dogs and would do best in a home with another dog to play with, large or small, he doesn't care.

Chase's adoption fee includes his/her 1st grooming/bath, spay/neuter, rabies and distemper vaccinations, fecal, heartworm tests, flea/tick treatment if required, microchip, collar, and any other vet care that's required during his/her stay with us.  Adoption Donation is:  $300

Please fill out an application at cryforhelprescue.com if you are interested in meeting Chase.

See all our adoptable dogs and fill out an online application now at http://www.cryforhelprescue.com.  Be Our Fan On Facebook And Share Our Cause;  www.facebook.com/cryforhelpanimalrescue

animal.description:
Tuesday is an extremely smart and responsive girl that loves to run and chase the ball, bounding like a deer with her tongue and ears flying! This goofy but bashful girl needs a loving, patient, low-traffic, adult-only home to succeed; she has a history of being uneasy with new people and apartment life would be too stressful for this sensitive girl. Tuesday is a very loving lady who will bond strongly to her person (can you say "BFFL"?) and would prefer a home where she can be your constant companion. She would love to both curl up with you on the couch AND also go on mountain adventures, swim in the river, chase the ball, or go on a trail run. She may prefer to be the only pet -- cats are just so much fun to chase, and though she has played successfully with other pups outside of the home in the past, she can have trouble sharing her belongings with canine companions. If Tuesday sounds like the right fit for you, please fill out a Pet & People profile!

COVID-19 Adoption Health and Safety:

While we remain closed for walk-ins, adoptions by appointment are available Wednesday and Friday - Monday.

First step for interested adopters is filling out our online Pet & People profile at www.myhswm.org,

*NEEDS ANOTHER DOG/NEEDS A YARD* SPECIAL NEEDS*Hello - I'm Ollie! I'm a Maltese/Papillon mix that is 6 years old and 6 pounds of adorableness! I.C.A.R.E. Dog Rescue found me in the shelter when I was super skinny and looking for a family. With lots of love and care, I've been filling out and discovering what this world has to offer. My vision is impaired, I can't see very well so it will take me a while to learn how to navigate the house. I still bump into chairs and the wall sometimes but I know how to use the doggy door and do my business. I have two eye medications so whoever adopts me will need to give me drops and ointment 2 times a day for the rest of my life. But trust me, I'm worth it! I discovered that I love toys and my favorites kinds are: crinkly toys, hard chewy toys and squeaky toys-in that order. I love being around adults, teens and kids. I also LOVE to play with my foster brothers - I can play all day long so if you have other playful dogs, you're the family for me because I will fit right in. When I'm not playing with my siblings, my most favorite thing to do is cuddle with my person and I must insist that I sleep in your arms every night. Let me show you how much I will love you and I will always want to be with you and will follow you to the ends of the earth. Be sure to watch my video!

If you are interested in adopting, please visit the I.C.A.R.E. Dog Rescue website and complete an adoption application: www.icaredogrescue.org/ready-to-adopt

animal.description:
Beau is a sweet & smart Shepherd/Lab mix who is 9 years old and weighs 55 lbs.  He is a gentle, calm, affectionate boy with low-medium energy who likes kids, has good leash manners and is currently learning basic commands in his foster home.  He would like to be an only dog and he is housebroken, crate trained, neutered, fully vaccinated & microchipped.  A home with a fenced yard or possibly a retired couple who likes to walk daily would be ideal.  Beau is HW+ so he is currently available for a foster-to-adopt situation until his HW treatment is complete and he is medically cleared for adoption. If you are not familiar with Heartworm disease, dogs get it from mosquitos and it is not contagious. It is easily prevented and highly treatable, but requires extended rest during treatment.

For more information about Beau, please email us at info@barkvilledogrescue.org. If you would like to adopt this sweet boy, please submit an application for him at https://www.barkvilledogrescue.org/applications

animal.description:
Please note donations using the SPONSOR ME tab will not go to Fluffy Dog Rescue.

To Locate Our Application go to http://rescue.fluffydog.net/how-to-adopt.html

Our listings are updated throughout the day. If there is an applicant, it will say PENDING ADOPTION next to the dog's name. If not, please submit an Application that can be found on our site, www.fluffydog.net. 

MY AGE: approx.  8 months (1/8) WEIGHT: approx. 18 lbs.  WHERE I AM FROM: AL (arrival 1/9) 

MY STORY: Scruffy is an adorable boy that loves people. With that said, he is a shy dog when he first meets people and for some time after that. If he is pushed, he could bite, therefore, we will not place him in a home with children under 16 years of age. We are also only adopting to people who have dog experience. They will need to have patience with him and he will be great. He will always be wary of people who are new in the home and should not be pushed to interact with them. In his own time he will adjust to his surroundings. Because of this he is considered a flight risk. He can never be offleash and would not do well at a dog park. We also will not adopt him to multi-family living situations or busy locations, as that will just heighten his fears.

He loves tennis balls .  His favorite game is picking up ones I roll to toward him and taking them into his area.

He seems to love all dogs and is wary of humans.  He walks great on a leash and would go for miles.  He loves to cuddle up with me and is very aware of everything going on.  So far he is very quiet.

He is wary of strange sounds and unexpected movements.  He cowers in a ball and might emit a low growl.  A gentle voice, slow movement, and a bit of eye contact and he let's me comfort him.  He gives kisses and willing licks strangers hands when he are on a walk.

This dog does shed and is not hypoallergenic.

HOUSEBROKEN?   GOOD WITH DOGS? Yes   GOOD WITH CATS?unknown

ADOPTION FEE: $650

To adopt the FIRST STEP is to complete an APPLICATION. The application can be found on our site www.fluffydog.net, or by clicking on the purple Fluffy Dog Rescue wording found in the left corner of this page under the dogs name.

Our dogs are located in foster homes throughout the state. We do not have a facility. Adopters must be 24 years old.We can not adopt to families with children under the age of six. We also adopt in WI, IL, and parts of MN. Most of our dogs are strays, so the breed is our best guess.
WI License #270548.
 
Check out Fluffy Dog Wellness on our Home Page. Great Solutions to Enhance Your Pet's Health. www.fluffydog.net

animal.description:
Medical note: I am heartworm positive. I will need to be treated with 28 days of doxycycline (an inexpensive antibiotic) before I receive my heartworm injections. You can still adopt me, but the cost of the treatment will become your responsibility, ODHS always recommends you contact a vet to price this treatment if you are interested in adopting me beforehand. I am also Ehrlichia positive, which is a tick-borne disease. I will need to be treated with 28 days of doxycycline (an antibiotic).

Who is looking for that sweet girl with the sweetest loving face? I am totally your girl! 

I am Maisey! I am 5 years old and 54 lbs! All I have to offer is love! I came here under weight and in need of TLC. Well, I hit the jackpot here. I have gotten such good care that I am already back up to a good weight and looking for my forever loving home. I haven't had a ton of experience in a house so I am learning that now. I have been doing really well! My house manners are getting there quickly. 

I don't mind my crate. I am shy at first, but once I see all you want to do is love me that is all it takes. I have 7 dogs in my foster home and I get along with them all. There are also two 9 yr old girls as well and they are great! 

I am learning to play with toys and so far enjoying it too. I am still learning better leash manners cause I get a little nervous and will pull. I tend to prefer female caregivers because that is what I am used to.  I have been known to show fear when it comes to interacting with men.
      
If you are looking for a dog with just a sweet, gentle soul, I am your girl!

You can still come adopt me or even join our foster program to help the humans learn all the awesome things about new dogs like me! Learn more on our website! 

Hope to see you soon! 

What breed am I? Mixed mutt! ODHS does not breed label (unless there’s official paperwork), as studies show it is nearly impossible to tell the exact breed of each dog based off of their appearance.

Educational articles:
3/3/3 Rule;
https://www.rescuedogs101.com/bringing-new-dog-home-3-3-3-rule/?fbclid=IwAR2iv5m7fqk3FieO7LOsstGeGsYYV_F1rJOd1BPxaImofLpcinpYsUbFRWs

Adoption Donations are $250 for an adult, $350 for puppies (a dog under one year of age), and $125 for a senior dog (based on the age of the dog). Adoption donations are to be made via cash, and credit/debit card. There is a $5 fee to run cards.

Please remember to bring a collar and leash (non-retractable) with you the day of the adoption. Note: Martingale collars and slip leads are strongly recommended.

Due to COVID19, we aren't having as many open, public adoption events.  Current schedule is pre-determined meet and greet appointments are Wednesday evenings and on Saturdays. 
Our adoption center is located at 3602 Lafayette Blvd, Suite 102, Fredericksburg, VA 22408. It's important that you keep an eye on your emails for any changes or updates during the adoption process.

Visit our website for an application to adopt. 
https://www.olddominionhumanesociety.org/adoption-application

Old Dominion Humane Society is a volunteer based organization. We are run completely by volunteers, who also have full time jobs, so we appreciate your patience.  Currently, the average timeframe for a response to your application is 1 week.

Like us on Facebook "Old Dominion Humane Society"
and be a part of promoting forever homes for dogs in need.
#Adopt #Donate #Foster #Volunteer 

Note: ODHS only adopts to Virginia and surrounding states (including D.C.). A $50 out of state fee applies.

It is the easiest way to start the communication and adoption process.Meet Jasper! Let's be honest, this soft and cuddly land seal isn't exactly lacking in the looks department - he is gorgeous! Jasper is a giant love bug who is exceptionally affectionate, and even a bit needy. His perfect family is one who would appreciate this and have lots of time to spend with him. As a young dog, Jasper is curious, playful, and exuberant, with a little energy to burn. An active family who has a fenced-in yard and wants an exercise partner would also be perfect for this stunner.

Jasper is an AMAZING pup, who is energetic, fun, friendly, and incredibly smart! He needs someone who is equally amazing and committed to shaping him into the best version of himself. Jasper is a diamond in the rough, but full of potential and the right forever family will be lucky to polish him up. He is young and exuberant, but also incredibly sweet and so excited about EVERYTHING, including training! Like most adolescents, Jasper would thrive in a family who was enthusiastic about continuing to work with him, allowing him to settle into a home, and giving him time to mature a little. He will, in turn, pay them back with love, loyalty, and lots of kisses.

Jasper was in the shelter for several months. Some dogs are able to handle that stress, but others, like Jasper, struggle fiercely with the environment. The result? He needs time and consistency to decompress and start to feel safe and secure once again. His perfect family would be committed to helping him be successful, which means give him the time and space he needs to be comfortable in new situations and not putting him in situations he's not ready for. Jasper has a good history of living with a cat, but he may be too excited now based on how stressed he got while in the shelter. He also has a good history playing with dogs, but might be a challenge to manage his training and integrating with another dog currently until he is on more stable ground, so he should be the only dog in the home. But don't worryreceiving all of his love and attention is a full time job. Due to his size and lack of manners currently, older or no kids would be best for this loveable pup.www.pittieloverescue.org

Please consider a donation so that we may continue the important work we do.
1/31/21 6:15 PM

animal.description:
Medical note: I am heartworm positive. I will need to be treated with 28 days of doxycycline (an inexpensive antibiotic) before I receive my heartworm injections. You can still adopt me, but the cost of the treatment will become your responsibility, ODHS always recommends you contact a vet to price this treatment if you are interested in adopting me beforehand.

Hi my name is Collette! I’m 4 years old and 32 lbs! 

I'm a bit shy. I have what you call fear aggression, it's when I'm cornered and that fight or flight kicks in - I'm gonna fight. I bit one guy on the hand when he took me outside and tried to put me in an outdoor pen and I didn't want to go, so my collar was too loose, so I popped out of it and ran off. Well, he tackled me to the ground and I got super scared so I bit his hand (1/22). 

Once I get home with you, I'm super loving and want all the pets! Don't move too fast though, cuz I get nervous. I am super smart and learned how to use a doggie door right away! If you slowly put a leash on me, I'll go in the crate, although I don't bark, I can be whiney. I'm a curious girl and wanna know what you are doing all the time! 

Hope to see you soon! 
Collette

What breed am I? Mixed mutt! ODHS does not breed label (unless there’s official paperwork), as studies show it is nearly impossible to tell the exact breed of each dog based off of their appearance.

Educational articles:
3/3/3 Rule;
https://www.rescuedogs101.com/bringing-new-dog-home-3-3-3-rule/?fbclid=IwAR2iv5m7fqk3FieO7LOsstGeGsYYV_F1rJOd1BPxaImofLpcinpYsUbFRWs

Adoption Donations are $250 for an adult, $350 for puppies (a dog under one year of age), and $125 for a senior dog (based on the age of the dog). Adoption donations are to be made via cash, and credit/debit card. There is a $5 fee to run cards.

Please remember to bring a collar and leash (non-retractable) with you the day of the adoption. Note: Martingale collars and slip leads are strongly recommended.

Due to COVID19, we aren't having as many open, public adoption events.  Current schedule is pre-determined meet and greet appointments are Wednesday evenings and on Saturdays. 
Our adoption center is located at 3602 Lafayette Blvd, Suite 102, Fredericksburg, VA 22408. It's important that you keep an eye on your emails for any changes or updates during the adoption process.

Visit our website for an application to adopt. 
https://www.olddominionhumanesociety.org/adoption-application

Old Dominion Humane Society is a volunteer based organization. We are run completely by volunteers, who also have full time jobs, so we appreciate your patience.  Currently, the average timeframe for a response to your application is 1 week.

Like us on Facebook "Old Dominion Humane Society"
and be a part of promoting forever homes for dogs in need.
#Adopt #Donate #Foster #Volunteer 

Note: ODHS only adopts to Virginia and surrounding states (including D.C.). A $50 out of state fee applies.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Welcome to Cocker Nation Rescue of Michigan!

Don't forget to visit our channel at YoutubeI'd like you to meet Roscoe(tricolor) and Henry(sable) 10.5 years old.
They are 1/2 brothers and a bonded pair, been together since pups. They will need to be placed together, no exception.
They came to Cocker Nation Rescue when their elderly owner could no longer care for them. They are house broken(no accidents). Since I have had them.
I'll tell you about Roscoe first:
Again, he is tricolored. He has recently lost 20 lbs. At his heaviest weight he was 60 lbs. He was diagnosed with thyroid issues and placed on thyroid med and in a matter of months has dropped down to 42 lbs. He gets thyroid meds Am and PM. He has dry eye issues so he gets drops in his eyes 3-4 times a day. He loves to go on walks and is a huge fan of a good message!! He tends to be the leader of the two. No bad habits or vices.
Henry, sable colored, is a lover boy! As sweet as they come! He has a slight limp from a broken leg as a puppy that required surgery. It doesn't slow him down. He also loves his walks and messages! Roscoe is Henry's security blank... Henry receives a lot of comfort and confidence through Roscoe. Henry is the follower. No bad habits or vices.
Added note: Henry can not be crated... his anxiety sky rockets and he could severely hurt himself while crated. Roscoe doesn't mind being crated.
They both take an allergy pill once a day which helps with itchy skin.
If you think these two beautiful boys could be just what you're looking for we'd love to here from you! They have a lot of love to give. We're not sure of their experience with cats. Their ideal home would offer daily walks, have a fenced yard. Possibly a retired person or a person working from home to give them the attention they deserve.(although they do well when left home alone).

Ready to add this duo to your life? Please fill out an application on our website! Or message us for more questions!

animal.description: Rosie #7596 is a 5-year-old female Labrador mix. Rosie is a shy but sweet lady. Rosie knows the commands: sit, stay and down. Her favorite treats are beef sticks, milk bones, bacon flavor and peanut butter. She walks well on a leash, although she does tend to cower around others. We are seeking an experienced dog owner. She has anxiety which makes her appear scared of other dogs and people. She is currently taking daily medication to help with her anxiety. This may or may not be a lifelong ailment. Due to her timid nature, she should be the only pet in the home. She should also be in a home without children. Rosie is both a flight risk and an escape artist. This means that she needs to be watched closely and always secured, whether that be on a leash outside or in her crate at home. Her perfect fit would be someone who is home most of the time so that she can always have a companion. Ideally, we would like to see her with an owner who is patient and willing to help her to come out of her shell. She weighs 50 pounds and should gain 5 pounds. This pup is microchipped. We believe you can always teach an ‘old’ dog new tricks, so we highly recommend continued obedience training for this smart pup; it stimulates the dog's mind and establishes a good dog/adopter relationship. This pup, like all pups, should be on heartworm preventative; an ounce of prevention is worth a pound of cure. If you are interested in adopting this dog, and are already approved to adopt through our organization, please contact dogs@lastchanceanimalrescue.org with the pup’s name and ID number in the subject line. OTHERWISE, please submit an adoption application online: http://www.lastchanceanimalrescue.org/adoptus.html E-mail dogs@lastchanceanimalrescue.org with questions. animal.description:
Umphrey and his siblings were born at Horse Creek on August 1, 2020. Their mother, Daisy, was rescued on June 9, 2020.  We were not aware that she was pregnant.  We are not sure who their fathers are, but all eight puppies are gorgeous!
 
Umphrey is one of six boys.  He is a playful, sweet puppy.  He and his siblings, Purvis, Qford, and Verge, favor so much it is hard to tell them apart!  He and his siblings have been lovingly cared for from birth and are going to make great family pets.  They are all extremely friendly and have never had a bad day.  They love people and love to romp and play in the grass.  

Umphrey is patiently waiting for his forever home.  He wants a family that will love and care for him always!  

All of our dogs are spayed or neutered and current on all vaccinations. They receive monthly heartworm and flea/tick prevention. All of their medical needs are taken care of before they are available for adoption. Our adoption fee is $100.00. Please complete an application, if you have found a dog you are interested in adopting. You can find our application at www.horsecreekwildlife.org/applic.html. Once completed, you can forward it to adoptions@horsecreekwildlife.org or fax it to 731-926-3000. Kim Austin, our adoption facilitator, will be in contact with you as soon as she has an opportunity to review your application. Understand that she has other duties and she will not ignore any interest shown in adopting one of our dogs. An application will need to be approved before a scheduled time to visit our dogs will be set up.  It may take up to 48 hours before she returns your call or responds to your email, due to work schedules, holidays and adoption events. We do the very best we can for the dogs we have rescued and do not take the adoption process lightly. Please be patient and understand that we will place our rescued dogs in the very best homes possible and reserve the right to refuse applications.
