animal.description:
APPLY ON OUR ADOPTION APPLICATION AT LEADRESCUE.ORG. WE DO NOT ADOPT OUT OF STATE. WE ONLY ADOPT IN ILLINOIS AND WITHIN 50 MILES OF DOWNTOWN CHICAGO.

Although my son has 4 built in dogs since birth, I hope he loves dogs and wants to take care of them as much as his mom does. And if not, well it’s not like my husband helped that much with them anyways. #boysgottagrowintomensomeday

Emilio and Sasha were posted on a veterinary office’s FB page because their family wanted a better life for them. The parent worked a lot of long hours and her family was not taking on enough responsibility for these two dogs while she was gone. It is a bummer that the person who is making sure there is bread on the table, had to go this direction. She 1,000% loved her babies.
LEAD was tagged and in 5 minutes, we were on our way to getting 2 more LEADers. I work kinda fast.

As you gaze upon their pictures, I want to thoroughly get this across: they are BONDED. Emilio the 4 year old, 80 lb Border Collie Lab adores his Sasha, the 9 year old, 12 lb Yorkiepoo and there is absolutely no way we could divorce them. Emilio is protective of shy Sasha when meeting other dogs to make sure no other dog gets with his woman. Sasha will even start barking to instigate and it gets the big bro all riled up. But otherwise, still friendly after the excitement dies down. They also both enjoy play fighting and we know Emilio let’s his lil sista win. When Sasha wants to cuddle with people, Emilio says don’t forget about me too! So one hand per dog is just not enough. One lap isn’t enough. Might have to break out those feet to work double time.

Emilio needs to be on a specific diet (he is on Hills from the vet) as he is allergic to rice, oats, soybean, peanuts, beef, eggs, and green peas. At this rate almost seems like cooking him some human food would be the only type of treats to reward him with. He is overweight a bit even with all those restrictions, so diets don’t necessarily work! He is also allergic to cats and dust. So no cats obvi and clean your house for Emilio’s sake, even under the dreaded couch. Hey I found an entire CostCo sized bottle of Aleve my husband lost under ours. Emilio might be on to something, helping husbands to not be blamed for everything. Sasha can eat anything, thank goodness. Bonded and is allergic to everything? Lol you guys, well Emilio, are too much.

Even though these pooches lost their home, at least they have each other to get through this. It wasn’t like one dog got to stay and the other got the boot. I could see the many reasons why Emilio would meet the boot, however. We need that special someone who is ready for both. Perhaps grateful children who have been dying for a dog and would wash their dishes and eat the broccoli, for their chance at owning 2 furry babies. So if interested in an allergy prone, protective, chunky big brother and a dog named Sasha, please apply at leadrescue.org!

animal.description: Nyla has affectionately earned the nickname "The Velveteen Potato" at our shelter for her adorably small and petit body and super soft (and beautiful) fur! This little nugget of gold came to us from a high volume shelter in Philadelphia when she was surrendered by her owners. They claimed they couldn't care for her anymore- but it looks like she has been a momma a few times over and we are happy that those days are gone! She can be a little shy at first but quickly warms up with EVERYONE! Due to her shy nature she would be best with children ages 12 and up, and a quiet household. She unfortunately cannot go into a home with cats as she does have a high prey drive. She LOVES to play with toys and is great with sharing them! As for her dog friends- she would need a quiet, submissive male (or the only princess in her castle!) Her adoption fee is $295 and that includes she is spayed, microchipped, and up to date on all vaccines, flea/tick treatments, and heartworm preventative. animal.description:
Toby is a handsome 9 year old black lab.  He is gentle and mild mannered.  He is a sweet old soul. Toby is looking for a forever where he can retire and spend his golden years being loved on and spoiled like all seniors should be. 

Toby is super smart and knows how to sit, stay, come, and down (lay down).  He can even play dead! And as you can see, balance treats on his nose!  He is up for a game of fetch when he's feeling frisky. He is not great on a leash, because he will pull if something sparks his interest.  He would do best in a home with a fenced yard where he can mosey at his leisure.  He enjoys being outside on pretty days and enjoys the cooler weather.  He is not a fan of 100+ degree days in July/August! (But seriously...who is? I know I don't like to be hot and sweaty!)

Toby is ok with calm, well mannered, older dogs. He does not appreciate puppies that pester him and get in his face.  He is too old and set in his ways to appreciate the activity level on a young, high energy dog.  We are unsure how he would do with cats as he's never met one before. Toby would do best in an adult only home or a home with children 12 yrs and up.  He is not impressed with the toddler he is living with right now and the baby doesn't understand how to appropriately interact with an older dog.

Toby is fully vetted, up to date on vaccines, has been tested for heartworm and is neutered.

Please email sharonrunkel@yahoo.com for more info about Toby and how to set up a meet and greet with this sweet old man.

animal.description: Max is a 1 year old dog that loves humans and loves to play! He is about 50 lbs and really strong but he is super sweet and loves to be pet. He likes to go on walks and does not get tired easily. Max would do best with a family that either has a large yard for him to run around or has time to take him on long walks. He does great with all humans including kids.

animal.description:
Courtesy Post

Hi, my name is Zuko! My birthday is 12/02/18. I am an American Pitbull Terrier and I weigh about 60 lbs. I am up to date on my vaccines and I take my Flea & Tick and Heartworm meds every month. I love going on car rides, playing outside, playing fetch with my inside toys, snuggling, sleeping on the couch, alone time in my crate (my choice) and having my hiney and inner back thighs scratched, I'll even lift my leg a little to help you get to the spot. 
I love to eat ice cubes, frozen carrots, peanut butter and cheese. I know commands like, sit, stay, wait, come, no, home (for my crate), out, food, are you hungry? and paw. I will tell you when it is time to go out and when I went to come back inside, I’m housebroken. 
I love to be the center of attention and prefer to be the only pet so I hope that you are ready for that and all the love I have to give! 

If you’re interested in adopting me, please visit www.almosthomeli.org for an application.

animal.description:
Riley is a very sweet beautiful adult female who was rescued from New Mexico after having many litters and then abandonded. She is very sweet and lived with cats but since owner was not home she was able to eat cat food and get sick. She is a food motived pup who is on Fat Dog Food to manage her weight. We have done blood tests which do not indiciate any medical. This is a lovely smaller shepherd with more characteristics of a Carolina Dog. She is great with other dogs.
She  must have a fenced yard, We prefer she lives with a family who has someone at home with her. She has not had a great history and really wants to be with her humans.  No exceptions.

animal.description:
Hello everyone meet Gunner! This 5 year old-ish Lab/Border Collie mix boy is about 55 lbs and will melt right into your lap and heart. Gunner had a rough start in his life but he is appreciative of everyone and everything around him. He loves to talk walks and it is truly awesome to watch him roll in the snow. Gunner enjoys being around people but is going to do best in a home where he is the only pet. Gunner is learning the crate is a safe place and he is doing really well at house breaking. If you are looking for an adult pup who gives as much as he gets, Gunner is your man!


Gunner should be the only dog in a home with a large fenced in yard and an active family. If the home has no fence the owners much commit to taking him for many walks and getting plenty of exercise.  


The adoption fee of $300 will include spay/neuter, microchip, age appropriate/required vaccinations, treatment for heartworm and any other necessary medical treatment to assure a healthy new pup for your family.


IMPORTANT DISCLAIMER: Although we do our best to describe breed, since our pups all come from shelters we can not and will not make any guarantee on breed or size. We can tell you that they are 100% RESCUED! And that is the BEST breed!

If you are interested in adopting/meeting , please visit our website at www.starfishanimalrescue.com or you may complete the online adoption application on our Facebook Page https://www.facebook.com/starfishanimalrescue/app/134425496630143/?ref=page_internal Once you complete and submit your dog adoption application we will set up an appointment to meet this pup!

*please note that we are a foster home based rescue and we do home visits as part of the adoption process - we are unable to adopt to families who live outside of the Chicago and surrounding suburbs. Thank you for your understanding.

animal.description:
Rikko is quite the looker! This gorgeous boy came to our shelter originally a scared, trembling mess. With the help of a dedicated foster mom, he has thrived and learned how to be a dog that is safe and loved. Rikko gets along well with other friendly dogs and doesn't appear to mind cats. Despite being 9 years old, he still loves to run and play and will do anything for a squeaky toy. He has been very sweet and gentle with new people he meets, but can still get a bit nervous with quick movements. Due to this, we're recommending that his new home have no small children. Rikko requires another canine friend in his new home to help him feel secure and to show him the ropes. 

If you're interested in meeting or adopting Rikko, please complete an application at: inapl.org/adoption-application. Once it's processed, a member of our team will be in touch with you to schedule a meet and greet appointment. This is the time when you and all members of your household will come to our shelter to officially make your connection with Rikko.

Rikko
Pit Bull Terrier mix
DOB: 12/1/2011
Weight: 60 lbs.

animal.description:
Hello! I'm Simba! I am very energetic, despite being up there in age, and I absolutely love to play. Tennis balls are my favorite, I love playing fetch! I also love going on my daily walks, and I keep my kennel clean and tidy. I have a genetic condition called pannus. This effects my eyes, and as a result I have pretty terrible vision. I get around pretty good though, and don't let it stop me from being a sweet and playful companion. I'll need daily eye medication to help my eyes, and the vets can tell you more about it if you call and ask for information. 

To find out more about me you can fill out a pre-adoption survey on our website, then email it to us. Then, call (816) 325-7207 (ext.2) and ask to make an appointment for a digital meeting! I can't wait to meet you!

https://www.ci.independence.mo.us/AnimalServices/AdoptableAnimals
